1
00:00:56,021 --> 00:00:58,067
WOMAN: Babe, are you out here?

2
00:00:58,359 --> 00:00:59,277
Yeah.

3
00:00:59,654 --> 00:01:01,240
Thought you might be.

4
00:01:01,281 --> 00:01:02,618
I have to go soon.

5
00:01:02,660 --> 00:01:03,745
Okay. Okay, I'm comin'.

6
00:01:05,039 --> 00:01:06,417
Come say goodbye to me.

7
00:01:06,459 --> 00:01:08,045
-Coffee?
-Good call.

8
00:01:08,087 --> 00:01:09,172
Would you make one
while I finish packing?

9
00:01:09,214 --> 00:01:10,091
Of course.

10
00:01:16,813 --> 00:01:17,815
(COFFEE MAKER WHIRRING)

11
00:01:23,451 --> 00:01:24,912
Car should be here in a minute.

12
00:01:25,747 --> 00:01:27,835
(TELEVISION CHATTER)

13
00:01:27,877 --> 00:01:29,297
Oh, thank you.

14
00:01:29,338 --> 00:01:31,176
(WHISPERING) Oh, my God.

15
00:01:31,217 --> 00:01:32,971
WOMAN ON TV: West bound is
experiencing heavy traffic...

16
00:01:33,013 --> 00:01:34,515
starting from the 610

17
00:01:34,557 --> 00:01:36,352
Garret road exit
and stretching...

18
00:01:36,394 --> 00:01:38,523
What am I gonna do without
your coffee for five days?

19
00:01:38,565 --> 00:01:41,154
-They have coffee in London.
-Do they?

20
00:01:41,613 --> 00:01:43,617
You sound really sure
for somebody who's never been.

21
00:01:43,658 --> 00:01:45,872
Five days?
I thought you said four.

22
00:01:45,914 --> 00:01:47,792
Yeah. Four days there, and then
I'm back on the overnight.

23
00:01:48,836 --> 00:01:49,838
Oh, right.

24
00:01:51,216 --> 00:01:52,426
You can still come, you know.

25
00:01:53,011 --> 00:01:54,681
I can't.

26
00:01:54,723 --> 00:01:57,479
I mean, there's somethin'
I'm tryin' to untangle at work.

27
00:01:57,520 --> 00:01:59,106
Oh, come on.

28
00:01:59,148 --> 00:02:01,695
Just this once. Take a risk.

29
00:02:02,321 --> 00:02:03,699
Next time. I promise.

30
00:02:03,741 --> 00:02:05,536
Mm-hm.

31
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:08,668
This is a list of things
that need to be watered.

32
00:02:08,709 --> 00:02:10,338
Thursday morning,
don't forget to leave your key

33
00:02:10,380 --> 00:02:11,674
for Mike and his son
for the boiler.

34
00:02:11,715 --> 00:02:12,634
Right.

35
00:02:12,676 --> 00:02:13,761
-(HORN HONKS)
-Mm.

36
00:02:14,596 --> 00:02:17,143
Uh, those should last
until I get home.

37
00:02:17,185 --> 00:02:18,271
Remind you of me.

38
00:02:19,898 --> 00:02:21,110
Don't need reminding.

39
00:02:21,151 --> 00:02:22,445
No?

40
00:02:22,487 --> 00:02:23,781
Are you sure
you're gonna be okay?

41
00:02:23,823 --> 00:02:25,118
I'll be fine.

42
00:02:25,159 --> 00:02:26,203
Come on.

43
00:02:26,997 --> 00:02:27,915
Love you.

44
00:02:28,416 --> 00:02:29,751
-Bye.
-Bye.

45
00:02:29,793 --> 00:02:31,213
(LAUGHING) Bye.

46
00:02:31,255 --> 00:02:32,382
(LAUGHS)

47
00:02:32,716 --> 00:02:34,344
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS)

48
00:02:34,386 --> 00:02:35,973
-(LAUGHS)
-(SHUTTER CLICKING)

49
00:02:36,348 --> 00:02:37,225
-Bye!
-Ooh.

50
00:02:38,311 --> 00:02:39,521
(LAUGHS)

51
00:03:15,594 --> 00:03:17,098
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

52
00:03:37,931 --> 00:03:39,100
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

53
00:03:41,604 --> 00:03:43,233
Good to see you, brother.
Yeah. Yeah.

54
00:03:43,275 --> 00:03:45,279
-Uh, oh! What's going on, Chuck?
-Hey.

55
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:47,868
Hey, you, uh--
you just back from somewhere?

56
00:03:47,909 --> 00:03:49,913
Across the pond, man.
Everywhere and nowhere.

57
00:03:49,955 --> 00:03:51,040
-You know how it is.
-Yeah.

58
00:03:51,082 --> 00:03:52,586
You just buzzin' in
and buzzin' out?

59
00:03:52,627 --> 00:03:54,798
Yeah. I got a day
of security debrief...

60
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:57,219
and then,
it's the home base, man.

61
00:03:57,261 --> 00:03:59,725
-Go kiss my little girl.
-Oh, that's important.

62
00:03:59,766 --> 00:04:01,353
Yeah. I just said
goodbye to my wife.

63
00:04:01,395 --> 00:04:02,606
Hey, man, what are you doing
for lunch today?

64
00:04:03,816 --> 00:04:05,110
-Nothin'. No, no plans.
-Yeah?

65
00:04:05,152 --> 00:04:06,489
Yeah. Yeah,
I'm completely free, man.

66
00:04:06,530 --> 00:04:07,616
That's great.

67
00:04:07,657 --> 00:04:08,951
You know,
I got this computer shit.

68
00:04:08,993 --> 00:04:10,538
Just a few, like, bits and bytes

69
00:04:10,580 --> 00:04:13,001
I would love to get that
big brain of yours to decipher.

70
00:04:13,043 --> 00:04:15,048
I swear, last time, bro,
you saved my life.

71
00:04:15,089 --> 00:04:16,509
-Yeah.
-Yeah?

72
00:04:16,550 --> 00:04:17,928
-Yeah, of course.
-Oh, that's great. All right.

73
00:04:17,969 --> 00:04:20,183
So, uh, you go ahead
and you eat your lunch,

74
00:04:20,225 --> 00:04:21,602
then I'll come get ya?

75
00:04:21,644 --> 00:04:23,231
-Yeah.
-My man.

76
00:04:23,272 --> 00:04:24,566
Tick tock, tick boom, bro.

77
00:04:27,572 --> 00:04:29,201
ELECTRONIC VOICE:
Floor Minus Two. Operations.

78
00:04:31,748 --> 00:04:33,167
-(SCANNER BEEPS)
-(BUTTON BEEPS)

79
00:04:38,887 --> 00:04:41,977
Floor Minus Five,
Decryption and Analysis.

80
00:04:49,241 --> 00:04:52,205
(KEYPAD BEEPING)

81
00:04:53,332 --> 00:04:55,211
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER)

82
00:05:25,899 --> 00:05:27,526
COMPUTERIZED VOICE:
Hello. Are you there, Charlie?

83
00:05:27,568 --> 00:05:30,115
What do you have for me today,
Señor Inquiline?

84
00:05:32,536 --> 00:05:34,624
COMPUTERIZED VOICE:
2.1 terabyte tranche.

85
00:05:34,667 --> 00:05:36,002
Kabul Station.

86
00:05:36,044 --> 00:05:38,758
2014 to 2022.

87
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:39,760
Open this alone.

88
00:05:40,094 --> 00:05:41,555
No charge this time.

89
00:05:46,607 --> 00:05:48,276
How's the weather in Istanbul?

90
00:05:49,488 --> 00:05:50,532
COMPUTERIZED VOICE: Nice try.

91
00:05:51,074 --> 00:05:52,284
It's just a matter of time.

92
00:05:52,911 --> 00:05:54,707
COMPUTERIZED VOICE: You think?

93
00:05:54,748 --> 00:05:57,379
It's been five years, Charlie,
and you're still guessing.

94
00:05:57,421 --> 00:05:58,631
CHARLIE: I'll get there.

95
00:05:58,673 --> 00:06:00,427
I like puzzles.

96
00:06:01,429 --> 00:06:03,433
COMPUTERIZED VOICE:
Not as much as
I like anonymity.

97
00:06:03,474 --> 00:06:04,810
If I had to guess,
you're a 50-year-old

98
00:06:04,852 --> 00:06:06,522
Russian man
living in Istanbul...

99
00:06:06,564 --> 00:06:07,899
with an affinity
for Reddit boards

100
00:06:07,941 --> 00:06:10,071
and Turkish coffee.

101
00:06:10,697 --> 00:06:12,826
COMPUTERIZED VOICE:
Perhaps, perhaps not.

102
00:06:12,868 --> 00:06:14,998
I'm serious.
Be careful with this data.

103
00:06:15,039 --> 00:06:17,502
It's highly compromising
for your agency.

104
00:06:17,544 --> 00:06:18,296
(COMPUTER BLIPS)

105
00:06:27,355 --> 00:06:28,274
(COMPUTER BLIPS)

106
00:06:31,698 --> 00:06:32,449
(COMPUTER BLIPS)

107
00:06:37,417 --> 00:06:38,921
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER)

108
00:06:38,962 --> 00:06:40,173
Hey.

109
00:06:40,215 --> 00:06:41,802
Hi, Team.

110
00:06:41,843 --> 00:06:43,889
Tell me again. How big
did you say the crate was?

111
00:06:43,931 --> 00:06:45,810
Twenty meters by 10.

112
00:06:45,851 --> 00:06:48,105
Another one
of Slater's hypotheticals.

113
00:06:48,147 --> 00:06:50,903
Satellite images of a crate
on the back of a semi-truck...

114
00:06:50,945 --> 00:06:53,617
rectangular in shape,
20 by 10 meters.

115
00:06:53,659 --> 00:06:54,869
Destination?

116
00:06:54,911 --> 00:06:56,581
A major metropolitan area.

117
00:06:56,623 --> 00:06:59,170
-Mm. LA.
-Wrong coast.

118
00:06:59,212 --> 00:07:00,548
Is the truck from Pennsylvania?

119
00:07:00,589 --> 00:07:02,552
Mm-hm.

120
00:07:02,593 --> 00:07:04,097
Headed to DC?

121
00:07:04,138 --> 00:07:05,516
So far, so good.

122
00:07:05,558 --> 00:07:06,685
-A flagpole.
-No, a missile.

123
00:07:06,726 --> 00:07:07,728
Christmas tree.

124
00:07:09,566 --> 00:07:11,611
The White House tree
always comes from a farm

125
00:07:11,653 --> 00:07:13,407
in Lehighton, Pennsylvania.

126
00:07:13,448 --> 00:07:15,369
And dimensions of the truck
tell the rest.

127
00:07:15,411 --> 00:07:16,413
He can be really
annoying sometimes.

128
00:07:16,454 --> 00:07:17,373
Wow.

129
00:07:17,665 --> 00:07:18,750
(MAN SIGHS)

130
00:07:20,462 --> 00:07:21,548
WOMAN: Oh, who's that?

131
00:07:21,924 --> 00:07:23,594
MAN: The most dangerous
man in the building.

132
00:07:23,635 --> 00:07:25,264
Secret agent. Bang, bang.

133
00:07:25,306 --> 00:07:26,391
He and Heller are besties.

134
00:07:26,433 --> 00:07:27,686
I'm his bestie.

135
00:07:27,728 --> 00:07:29,648
No. We're just,
uh, acquaintances.

136
00:07:30,107 --> 00:07:30,901
How do you know him?

137
00:07:32,445 --> 00:07:33,656
Saved his life.

138
00:07:44,762 --> 00:07:46,306
(COMPUTER BLIPS)

139
00:07:46,349 --> 00:07:48,268
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

140
00:07:49,772 --> 00:07:50,815
Heller.

141
00:07:50,857 --> 00:07:51,943
WOMAN: What are you wearing?

142
00:07:52,611 --> 00:07:53,821
Sarah?

143
00:07:53,863 --> 00:07:55,367
SARAH: No. Saddam Hussein.

144
00:07:56,577 --> 00:07:57,412
He's dead.

145
00:07:57,871 --> 00:07:59,208
Humor, Heller.

146
00:07:59,249 --> 00:08:00,460
CHARLIE: Right, right.

147
00:08:00,502 --> 00:08:01,921
I'm just calling
to let you know I'm here.

148
00:08:01,963 --> 00:08:03,675
Right. I know.
I-I know. I tracked you.

149
00:08:03,716 --> 00:08:04,843
SARAH:
I'd be hurt if you didn't.

150
00:08:04,885 --> 00:08:07,307
I'm just grabbing a coffee.

151
00:08:07,349 --> 00:08:08,851
Trying to keep me awake
a little bit longer

152
00:08:08,893 --> 00:08:10,438
while I wait
for the rest of the team.

153
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:12,442
All right. Take a walk.
Go get some fresh air, honey.

154
00:08:12,484 --> 00:08:14,279
But I want to lie down.

155
00:08:14,321 --> 00:08:16,158
No. If you lie down,
you'll never get up.

156
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:19,540
Oh. Is that-- is that sage
advice from the world traveler?

157
00:08:19,581 --> 00:08:20,835
Harsh.

158
00:08:20,876 --> 00:08:22,629
Hey, listen.
I'm on to something here.

159
00:08:22,671 --> 00:08:23,716
Can I call you later?

160
00:08:24,466 --> 00:08:26,554
Yeah. I love you.

161
00:08:26,595 --> 00:08:27,807
I love you, babe. Bye. Bye.

162
00:08:27,849 --> 00:08:29,226
-Bye. Bye.
-Bye.

163
00:08:29,268 --> 00:08:30,145
-Bye.
-Bye-bye.

164
00:08:33,944 --> 00:08:34,904
(COMPUTER BLIPS)

165
00:08:35,740 --> 00:08:37,618
(DISTANT CHATTER)

166
00:08:37,660 --> 00:08:38,871
(EXHALES NERVOUSLY)

167
00:08:40,833 --> 00:08:42,712
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER)

168
00:08:46,803 --> 00:08:49,183
(KEYPAD BEEPING)

169
00:09:06,301 --> 00:09:07,178
(COMPUTER BLIPS)

170
00:09:12,271 --> 00:09:13,023
(COMPUTER BLIPS)

171
00:09:40,829 --> 00:09:42,248
(COMPUTER BLIPS)

172
00:09:52,769 --> 00:09:53,897
(EXHALES)

173
00:09:56,402 --> 00:09:57,821
What the hell?

174
00:09:59,116 --> 00:10:01,662
REPORT There are witness
reports of a drone strike...

175
00:10:01,704 --> 00:10:05,670
but U.S. sources have confirmed
that it was a suicide bomber.

176
00:10:05,712 --> 00:10:07,257
The scale of the attacks
devastated...

177
00:10:07,299 --> 00:10:08,886
REPORTER 2:
Some 150 people killed...

178
00:10:08,928 --> 00:10:11,182
including French
special forces.

179
00:10:11,224 --> 00:10:13,686
Seven Danish marines
were killed in the explosion...

180
00:10:13,729 --> 00:10:16,693
which was initially reported
as a misdirected air strike.

181
00:10:16,735 --> 00:10:18,279
REPORTER 4: A Department
of Defense spokesman...

182
00:10:18,321 --> 00:10:21,244
denied reports of U.S. Air
Force operations in the area...

183
00:10:21,285 --> 00:10:23,122
blaming the attack
on local insurgents.

184
00:10:23,749 --> 00:10:25,168
CHARLIE: Chief Moore.

185
00:10:29,134 --> 00:10:30,387
(SIGHS)

186
00:10:33,602 --> 00:10:34,437
Hey, buddy.

187
00:10:35,815 --> 00:10:36,942
Carlos.

188
00:10:37,694 --> 00:10:38,946
You okay?
You look like a damn ghost.

189
00:10:38,988 --> 00:10:40,825
I was just rectifying some...

190
00:10:42,620 --> 00:10:43,580
Charlie?

191
00:10:43,622 --> 00:10:44,749
Some files.

192
00:10:45,293 --> 00:10:46,545
Okay.

193
00:10:46,962 --> 00:10:48,632
I may have looked somewhere
I shouldn't have.

194
00:10:48,674 --> 00:10:49,843
Within our department?

195
00:10:49,884 --> 00:10:50,970
Gray area.

196
00:10:51,012 --> 00:10:52,682
We don't do gray areas, Charlie.

197
00:10:52,724 --> 00:10:54,185
Our work is decidedly binary.

198
00:10:54,227 --> 00:10:55,855
Then, no.

199
00:10:55,896 --> 00:10:58,360
In that case,
what you do is you keep quiet.

200
00:10:58,402 --> 00:10:59,154
Yeah.

201
00:11:02,702 --> 00:11:03,787
(SCANNER BEEPS)

202
00:11:10,676 --> 00:11:12,931
(LINE RINGING)

203
00:11:14,059 --> 00:11:15,394
SARAH: Hey, I'm either busy
or dropped my cell

204
00:11:15,436 --> 00:11:16,981
at the bottom of my bag.

205
00:11:17,023 --> 00:11:18,902
Tell me who you are
and I'll call you back.

206
00:11:18,943 --> 00:11:21,156
-(LINE BEEPS)
-Hey, it's me.

207
00:11:21,198 --> 00:11:23,243
Um... Miss you.

208
00:11:23,787 --> 00:11:25,707
I will water
the flowers first thing.

209
00:11:27,544 --> 00:11:28,421
Call me.

210
00:11:32,471 --> 00:11:34,350
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

211
00:11:48,001 --> 00:11:49,088
(SCANNER BEEPS)

212
00:11:52,052 --> 00:11:53,721
-Chief Moore.
-Charlie.

213
00:11:54,723 --> 00:11:58,481
I'm sorry, I don't see you
down here very often, sir.

214
00:11:58,523 --> 00:11:59,275
Why would you?

215
00:12:00,527 --> 00:12:02,448
Nice office you have.

216
00:12:02,489 --> 00:12:04,870
Yeah. Yeah, if you don't like
sunlight or fresh air.

217
00:12:06,706 --> 00:12:09,211
For a moss or a lichen
or mushrooms...

218
00:12:09,253 --> 00:12:11,382
Charlie, have you been
tracking the news?

219
00:12:11,758 --> 00:12:14,096
Well, I'm still tryin' to find
an outlet I can trust.

220
00:12:14,472 --> 00:12:15,850
That's what we thought

221
00:12:15,892 --> 00:12:17,144
when we heard
you were here this morning.

222
00:12:17,896 --> 00:12:19,482
We?

223
00:12:19,524 --> 00:12:21,612
I need you to come with me
to the Director's office.

224
00:12:23,574 --> 00:12:24,618
Please.

225
00:12:25,285 --> 00:12:26,622
(ELEVATOR DINGS)

226
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:29,084
ELECTRONIC VOICE:
Floor Seven. Executive.

227
00:12:35,848 --> 00:12:36,808
Director.

228
00:12:41,276 --> 00:12:43,864
Director O'Brien,
this is Charlie Heller.

229
00:12:45,326 --> 00:12:46,370
-Hi.
-Hello, Charlie.

230
00:12:46,411 --> 00:12:47,372
Come have a seat.

231
00:12:47,622 --> 00:12:48,666
I'd rather not.

232
00:12:51,672 --> 00:12:54,844
Mr. Heller, I'm afraid
there was a situation in London.

233
00:12:56,098 --> 00:12:56,848
Have you heard?

234
00:12:57,600 --> 00:12:59,062
London?

235
00:12:59,104 --> 00:13:01,901
An attack at
the Christopher Street Hotel.

236
00:13:05,616 --> 00:13:07,036
-Charlie...
-No, no.

237
00:13:07,662 --> 00:13:09,541
I'm very sorry, Mr. Heller.

238
00:13:09,583 --> 00:13:11,253
What?

239
00:13:11,295 --> 00:13:13,132
-Your wife has been killed.
-No.

240
00:13:13,507 --> 00:13:14,927
No, she's at a conference.

241
00:13:14,969 --> 00:13:16,388
We should call her.

242
00:13:16,430 --> 00:13:17,473
Charlie, I'm very sorry
to give you this...

243
00:13:17,516 --> 00:13:19,144
Can we call her?
I have to call her.

244
00:13:20,062 --> 00:13:21,608
Charlie, I think
you need to see this.

245
00:13:22,693 --> 00:13:24,279
REPORTER: We're following
a breaking news story

246
00:13:24,321 --> 00:13:25,991
here in London...

247
00:13:26,033 --> 00:13:29,122
where a terrifying hostage
situation unfolded...

248
00:13:29,164 --> 00:13:32,128
at the Christopher Street Hotel
earlier today.

249
00:13:32,170 --> 00:13:34,925
Four assailants
stormed into the hotel,

250
00:13:34,967 --> 00:13:37,890
taking a number
of individuals hostage.

251
00:13:37,931 --> 00:13:41,481
Two individuals
sadly lost their lives...

252
00:13:41,522 --> 00:13:44,278
including an American woman
who was taken hostage...

253
00:13:44,320 --> 00:13:46,491
- It doesn't say it's her.
-...during the ordeal.

254
00:13:46,532 --> 00:13:47,660
Eyewitnesses report...

255
00:13:47,701 --> 00:13:48,912
Charlie, you have
to believe us.

256
00:13:48,954 --> 00:13:50,415
...a chaotic scene
inside the hotel

257
00:13:50,457 --> 00:13:52,002
as the perpetrators
forced their way...

258
00:13:52,044 --> 00:13:54,966
This is footage we pulled
from surveillance cams.

259
00:13:55,008 --> 00:13:57,262
...terrorized the guests
and the staff.

260
00:13:57,304 --> 00:13:59,810
One of the victims
has been identified.

261
00:13:59,851 --> 00:14:02,231
She is a 32-year-old
American woman...

262
00:14:02,272 --> 00:14:03,734
that was tragically
taken hostage

263
00:14:03,776 --> 00:14:05,112
by the assailants.

264
00:14:05,153 --> 00:14:06,657
The police are
not revealing her.

265
00:14:06,699 --> 00:14:07,992
(BREATHES SHAKILY)

266
00:14:09,996 --> 00:14:11,040
(INHALES SHARPLY)

267
00:14:20,183 --> 00:14:22,020
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER AND SHOUTS)

268
00:14:28,074 --> 00:14:29,661
It's all right.

269
00:14:29,703 --> 00:14:30,955
I got this.
Don't worry about it.

270
00:14:32,417 --> 00:14:34,504
-(OVERLAPPING SHOUTS)
-Charlie, Charlie, wait!

271
00:14:37,343 --> 00:14:39,473
Charles! Charles!

272
00:14:39,514 --> 00:14:41,810
(OVERLAPPING SHOUTS CONTINUE)

273
00:14:42,061 --> 00:14:43,773
REPORTER: Metropolitan
Police has initiated

274
00:14:43,814 --> 00:14:46,153
a citywide manhunt.

275
00:14:46,195 --> 00:14:48,157
They are working tirelessly
to locate the assailants...

276
00:14:48,199 --> 00:14:49,659
(CELL PHONE
RINGING AND VIBRATING)

277
00:14:49,701 --> 00:14:51,705
...and secure
the rescue and release...

278
00:14:51,747 --> 00:14:53,000
(RINGING AND VIBRATING STOPS)

279
00:14:53,042 --> 00:14:54,419
...of the-- the hostage...

280
00:15:26,693 --> 00:15:28,697
CHARLIE:
How can we not know more?

281
00:15:28,738 --> 00:15:30,492
This was in London...

282
00:15:30,826 --> 00:15:34,125
947,000 cameras.

283
00:15:34,166 --> 00:15:36,129
They drove into traffic.

284
00:15:36,170 --> 00:15:37,923
Nobody is getting
away with this.

285
00:15:37,965 --> 00:15:39,385
You have my word.

286
00:15:39,427 --> 00:15:40,512
Okay.

287
00:15:43,518 --> 00:15:45,188
Tell me what we know so far.

288
00:15:45,230 --> 00:15:46,942
Mr. Heller...

289
00:15:46,984 --> 00:15:50,365
with respect,
let us handle this.

290
00:15:50,741 --> 00:15:53,038
Forgive me, sir, I don't believe
we've officially met.

291
00:15:53,079 --> 00:15:55,542
I'm the one who's gonna ensure
that those who did this

292
00:15:55,584 --> 00:15:57,296
are held to account.

293
00:15:57,338 --> 00:15:59,885
And what would that look like,
sir, with respect...

294
00:16:01,054 --> 00:16:03,391
being "held to account"?

295
00:16:03,433 --> 00:16:05,980
Look, we can't get
into specifics yet.

296
00:16:07,274 --> 00:16:09,362
Of course, you understand that.

297
00:16:09,821 --> 00:16:13,537
We'll tell you what we can
as soon as we can.

298
00:16:13,913 --> 00:16:16,084
You just said
what he said, only nicer.

299
00:16:16,125 --> 00:16:18,046
Go home, Charlie.

300
00:16:18,088 --> 00:16:19,967
You need to take some time.

301
00:16:22,681 --> 00:16:24,559
(CRICKETS CHIRPING)

302
00:17:04,347 --> 00:17:06,268
(VEHICLE BEEPING)

303
00:17:16,581 --> 00:17:18,418
-Next of kin?
-Yes.

304
00:17:24,347 --> 00:17:26,226
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

305
00:18:17,412 --> 00:18:19,625
(SNIFFLING)

306
00:18:23,925 --> 00:18:26,430
(SOBS QUIETLY)

307
00:18:32,359 --> 00:18:33,861
(SOBS)

308
00:18:57,743 --> 00:18:59,622
(KEYBOARD CLACKING)

309
00:19:03,588 --> 00:19:05,718
-(KEY CLACKS)
-(OVERLAPPING SHOUTING)

310
00:19:07,805 --> 00:19:09,642
(INDISTINCT SHOUTS)

311
00:19:11,855 --> 00:19:13,942
(SARAH SCREAMS)

312
00:19:44,963 --> 00:19:46,675
(COMPUTER BLIPS)

313
00:19:46,717 --> 00:19:48,512
CHARLIE: The suspects arrived
via the service entrance

314
00:19:48,553 --> 00:19:50,349
around 11:00 hours.

315
00:19:50,391 --> 00:19:52,269
The vehicle had been
stolen overnight

316
00:19:52,311 --> 00:19:55,150
at about 01:24 in the East End.

317
00:19:55,192 --> 00:19:57,697
Prints, DNA,
all professionally scrubbed out.

318
00:19:58,031 --> 00:19:59,952
Four-person team.

319
00:19:59,993 --> 00:20:01,580
Appears they had a meeting...

320
00:20:01,622 --> 00:20:04,420
with Impact Investments
out of Indonesia on our radar.

321
00:20:04,461 --> 00:20:06,089
This is when it all started.

322
00:20:06,632 --> 00:20:08,636
Something must have
got heated inside,

323
00:20:08,678 --> 00:20:10,598
it spilled out
into the corridor.

324
00:20:10,640 --> 00:20:12,727
Impact's security
detail got jumpy,

325
00:20:12,978 --> 00:20:14,398
and one of the four drew on him.

326
00:20:15,065 --> 00:20:17,027
One dead, one critical.

327
00:20:17,320 --> 00:20:19,700
Hotel security are alerted, and
the police have been called.

328
00:20:20,785 --> 00:20:22,956
The suspects are now in a race
to leave the building...

329
00:20:23,749 --> 00:20:25,628
and they decided
to grab some insurance.

330
00:20:25,670 --> 00:20:26,797
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

331
00:20:26,839 --> 00:20:28,426
(GUNFIRE AND SCREAMS)

332
00:20:28,927 --> 00:20:30,555
Everyone! Get down!

333
00:20:30,597 --> 00:20:32,894
(OVERLAPPING SHOUTS)

334
00:20:32,935 --> 00:20:33,728
Everyone down.

335
00:20:36,192 --> 00:20:37,569
(INDISTINCT SHOUTS)

336
00:20:40,200 --> 00:20:41,243
SARAH: Get down. Get down.

337
00:20:41,285 --> 00:20:42,914
No, no, no. Run. Run.

338
00:20:42,955 --> 00:20:44,583
CHARLIE: They only took Sarah
because she tried

339
00:20:44,625 --> 00:20:45,794
to save someone else.

340
00:20:45,836 --> 00:20:48,842
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

341
00:20:50,763 --> 00:20:52,767
GUNMAN: (DISTORTED)
You do as I say. Move!

342
00:20:52,808 --> 00:20:53,977
(AUDIO REVERSES)

343
00:20:54,019 --> 00:20:55,271
You do as I say. Move!

344
00:20:56,357 --> 00:20:57,860
(COMPUTER BLIPS)

345
00:20:57,902 --> 00:20:59,697
GUNMAN: (CLEARER)
You do as I say. Move!

346
00:21:00,950 --> 00:21:03,789
CHARLIE: The man who took Sarah
is Mishka Blazhic.

347
00:21:03,830 --> 00:21:06,001
Origins in Belarus,
though often based in Moscow.

348
00:21:06,043 --> 00:21:07,755
(SCREAMS AND GUNFIRE)

349
00:21:07,797 --> 00:21:09,676
They fled the conference room
with three hostages.

350
00:21:10,761 --> 00:21:12,013
-(GUNSHOT)
-(AUDIO REVERSES)

351
00:21:12,055 --> 00:21:14,435
MAN: Stay down,
or I'll shoot you!

352
00:21:14,477 --> 00:21:15,312
(CLEARER) Stay down,
or I'll shoot you!

353
00:21:15,354 --> 00:21:17,149
(GUNSHOT)

354
00:21:17,191 --> 00:21:19,571
CHARLIE: This man, Lawrence
Ellish, is South African.

355
00:21:19,612 --> 00:21:21,449
Ex-special forces.

356
00:21:21,491 --> 00:21:23,912
Ellish seems to handle
shipments for the wider group.

357
00:21:24,455 --> 00:21:26,042
Armed police
and security were arriving

358
00:21:26,084 --> 00:21:27,753
from St. Pancras Station,

359
00:21:27,795 --> 00:21:30,384
but were ordered to hold back
because of the hostages.

360
00:21:32,848 --> 00:21:35,937
Police sealed off the area,
marksmen in position,

361
00:21:35,979 --> 00:21:38,650
but the suspects are exposed,
and they knew it.

362
00:21:38,692 --> 00:21:40,112
-(SIRENS)
-(INDISTINCT COMMANDS)

363
00:21:40,154 --> 00:21:41,323
OFFICER: Armed police!
Drop your weapons!

364
00:21:41,364 --> 00:21:42,366
OFFICER 2: Get down!

365
00:21:43,076 --> 00:21:45,582
-(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)
-SARAH: Let go of me! No!

366
00:21:46,207 --> 00:21:48,003
-(GASPING)
-(KEYBOARD CLICKS)

367
00:21:58,315 --> 00:22:00,987
CHARLIE: Sarah's killer
is harder to track.

368
00:22:01,029 --> 00:22:04,035
He seems to sense the cameras.
He says nothing.

369
00:22:04,286 --> 00:22:07,209
But I processed all the CCTV,
cell phones...

370
00:22:07,250 --> 00:22:08,920
dash cams, body cams...

371
00:22:08,961 --> 00:22:10,965
and the audio to give us a 360.

372
00:22:11,592 --> 00:22:13,221
And that provides us with an ID.

373
00:22:14,264 --> 00:22:16,143
This is Horst Schiller.

374
00:22:16,185 --> 00:22:19,149
Loose affiliations with dozens
of mercs and defense groups.

375
00:22:19,191 --> 00:22:20,944
I'm still filling that in.

376
00:22:20,986 --> 00:22:22,990
They seem to be
operating as interface

377
00:22:23,032 --> 00:22:25,955
between bad state actors
and terrorist entities.

378
00:22:25,996 --> 00:22:27,416
All business.

379
00:22:27,749 --> 00:22:29,461
And they keep getting hired.

380
00:22:30,296 --> 00:22:32,467
But for this one,
I have a current location.

381
00:22:32,509 --> 00:22:34,138
Gretchen Frank.

382
00:22:34,179 --> 00:22:36,267
Former Armenian IO.

383
00:22:36,517 --> 00:22:37,729
She's in Paris.

384
00:22:38,772 --> 00:22:40,525
Buys her bread at this cafe.

385
00:22:41,820 --> 00:22:42,697
Turns up there regularly.

386
00:22:51,548 --> 00:22:52,382
You knew this?

387
00:22:52,759 --> 00:22:53,677
Thank you.

388
00:22:54,971 --> 00:22:56,725
-We'll do a comparison.
-Wait.

389
00:22:57,602 --> 00:22:59,481
You already know
about Gretchen Frank?

390
00:22:59,522 --> 00:23:02,487
I understand you
wanna see progress, Charlie.

391
00:23:03,322 --> 00:23:05,659
But sometimes,
the best course of action...

392
00:23:06,453 --> 00:23:08,207
isn't always the most obvious.

393
00:23:08,248 --> 00:23:09,125
"Most obvious"?

394
00:23:09,167 --> 00:23:11,171
We want the whole network.

395
00:23:11,213 --> 00:23:13,091
The network has nothing
to do with Sarah.

396
00:23:13,133 --> 00:23:16,056
CALEB: But everything to do
with the sovereignty

397
00:23:16,097 --> 00:23:17,350
and security of this country.

398
00:23:18,018 --> 00:23:23,403
What you do is very important
to what we do, Charlie.

399
00:23:24,531 --> 00:23:27,328
We think it would be good
for you to see Dr. Garrison.

400
00:23:34,384 --> 00:23:36,513
Am I here for me or the Agency?

401
00:23:37,306 --> 00:23:41,064
It is important we assess you're
well enough to return to work.

402
00:23:41,106 --> 00:23:42,066
-Mm.
-Obviously.

403
00:23:43,736 --> 00:23:45,907
But you've suffered
a terrible loss.

404
00:23:46,909 --> 00:23:48,454
And we want to support you.

405
00:23:50,709 --> 00:23:53,005
Can you describe your feelings?

406
00:23:54,007 --> 00:23:55,134
Right now?

407
00:23:55,635 --> 00:23:58,056
You mean, denial, anger...

408
00:23:58,098 --> 00:23:59,142
acceptance...

409
00:24:01,272 --> 00:24:02,441
Say more.

410
00:24:05,822 --> 00:24:06,949
She's gone.

411
00:24:12,920 --> 00:24:14,340
Yeah, that she had
to go like that.

412
00:24:24,735 --> 00:24:27,867
And that I didn't speak to her
on the phone when she called.

413
00:24:30,121 --> 00:24:31,374
And you blame
yourself for that?

414
00:24:31,415 --> 00:24:32,292
Yes.

415
00:24:36,593 --> 00:24:38,722
For not going with her
when she asked me to,

416
00:24:38,764 --> 00:24:40,058
because I never do.

417
00:24:42,730 --> 00:24:43,732
Never did.

418
00:24:49,034 --> 00:24:50,454
And what is that
making you feel?

419
00:24:55,213 --> 00:24:56,425
Uh, pretty useless.

420
00:24:58,262 --> 00:24:59,514
A-Angry.

421
00:25:01,893 --> 00:25:03,439
Very, very angry.

422
00:25:09,659 --> 00:25:14,127
Uh, I gave the Agency
the names of Sarah's killers.

423
00:25:14,169 --> 00:25:15,588
They did nothing.

424
00:25:16,631 --> 00:25:18,343
-What do you want them to do?
-Their job!

425
00:25:20,014 --> 00:25:22,018
I want them to go
after Sarah's killers.

426
00:25:24,397 --> 00:25:25,776
Will that make you feel better?

427
00:25:27,028 --> 00:25:28,782
This shouldn't be about me.

428
00:25:28,823 --> 00:25:30,076
Sarah mattered.

429
00:25:32,205 --> 00:25:33,583
She deserves more.

430
00:25:35,211 --> 00:25:37,423
But in the end,
this is about you.

431
00:25:39,720 --> 00:25:40,639
Sarah's gone.

432
00:25:42,851 --> 00:25:45,649
You are gonna have to try
and come to terms with that.

433
00:25:48,446 --> 00:25:49,990
I can help.

434
00:25:51,661 --> 00:25:53,581
But only you can really
make things better.

435
00:26:01,430 --> 00:26:03,309
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

436
00:26:17,379 --> 00:26:18,631
(SCANNER BEEPS)

437
00:26:18,673 --> 00:26:19,758
ELECTRONIC VOICE:
Floor Minus Five.

438
00:26:19,801 --> 00:26:21,429
Decryption and Analysis.

439
00:26:21,470 --> 00:26:22,472
(COMPUTER BLIPS)

440
00:26:30,447 --> 00:26:31,909
MAN:
And the renovation schedule?

441
00:26:31,950 --> 00:26:33,036
We can discuss
the cryptography project.

442
00:26:48,107 --> 00:26:49,361
WOMAN:
Okay. All right. I can do this.

443
00:26:49,402 --> 00:26:51,365
MAN: Thanks.
I think we need to flag this.

444
00:26:51,907 --> 00:26:53,827
(PRINTER WHIRRING)

445
00:27:02,136 --> 00:27:03,389
(PRINTER BEEPS)

446
00:27:11,154 --> 00:27:12,282
(LAPTOP BEEPS)

447
00:27:20,006 --> 00:27:21,300
ELECTRONIC VOICE:
You've been very quiet lately.

448
00:27:21,884 --> 00:27:23,262
Guessed where I live yet?

449
00:27:38,125 --> 00:27:39,210
(SCANNER BEEPS)

450
00:27:40,672 --> 00:27:43,428
(INDISTINCT CHATTER ON TV)

451
00:27:43,470 --> 00:27:45,307
You good here
for a minute, buddy?

452
00:27:45,349 --> 00:27:46,851
I gotta close up the back.

453
00:27:46,893 --> 00:27:48,396
Oh, yeah. Yeah. I--

454
00:27:48,938 --> 00:27:50,192
I got you covered out here.

455
00:27:50,776 --> 00:27:52,696
(CHATTER CONTINUES ON TV)

456
00:28:05,055 --> 00:28:07,226
(ELEVATOR DINGS)

457
00:28:07,726 --> 00:28:09,605
ELECTRONIC VOICE:
Floor Seven. Executive.

458
00:28:16,661 --> 00:28:18,540
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

459
00:28:22,966 --> 00:28:26,598
I'm holding the highlights
of over 100 eyes-only cables.

460
00:28:26,849 --> 00:28:28,309
These are double coded
from a data cache

461
00:28:28,351 --> 00:28:29,729
out of Kabul Station.

462
00:28:29,771 --> 00:28:31,190
These are the official cables.

463
00:28:31,525 --> 00:28:34,029
Same dates, same events,

464
00:28:34,071 --> 00:28:37,745
except for very key information
that has been altered

465
00:28:37,787 --> 00:28:40,376
or completely scrubbed
from the record.

466
00:28:41,462 --> 00:28:42,630
What are you talking about?

467
00:28:46,095 --> 00:28:47,307
This is your cover-up.

468
00:28:47,724 --> 00:28:48,767
Have you lost your mind?

469
00:28:48,809 --> 00:28:50,605
To put it mildly.

470
00:28:50,646 --> 00:28:54,988
This is your order of operations
to destroy a hospital in Syria.

471
00:28:55,030 --> 00:28:57,327
An allied base in Yemen.

472
00:28:57,368 --> 00:28:58,997
An Afghani politician's house.

473
00:28:59,039 --> 00:29:00,166
MOORE:
You have no idea what...

474
00:29:00,208 --> 00:29:01,627
A border crossing in Somalia.

475
00:29:01,668 --> 00:29:04,090
I count more
than 1,000 casualties

476
00:29:04,132 --> 00:29:07,055
and over 400
civilian fatalities.

477
00:29:07,096 --> 00:29:09,768
It's only out of respect
for your recent loss

478
00:29:09,810 --> 00:29:12,190
that I'm not throwing you
out of this office.

479
00:29:12,232 --> 00:29:15,404
I'm just gonna tell you,
you don't have a goddamn clue.

480
00:29:15,446 --> 00:29:16,448
You see right here?

481
00:29:16,490 --> 00:29:17,701
The convoy?

482
00:29:18,912 --> 00:29:20,164
You targeted our allies.

483
00:29:21,333 --> 00:29:22,460
You false-flagged it.

484
00:29:22,502 --> 00:29:24,256
You got them all fired up

485
00:29:24,297 --> 00:29:25,341
and then sucked them
right back in

486
00:29:25,383 --> 00:29:26,761
where you wanted them.

487
00:29:27,095 --> 00:29:28,473
You were forcing mission creep.

488
00:29:28,515 --> 00:29:29,850
Okay. That's enough.

489
00:29:31,353 --> 00:29:32,565
"That's enough"?

490
00:29:33,148 --> 00:29:34,944
These were not
operational choices.

491
00:29:36,364 --> 00:29:39,202
You, sir, made
political decisions.

492
00:29:40,204 --> 00:29:42,585
And your signatures
are all over these.

493
00:29:42,626 --> 00:29:45,257
Here and-- and here.
And here. Here.

494
00:29:45,299 --> 00:29:47,970
You are so far
above your pay grade.

495
00:29:48,012 --> 00:29:49,640
Well, you're right.
You're right.

496
00:29:49,682 --> 00:29:51,018
Maybe we should...

497
00:29:51,644 --> 00:29:53,106
take this up with the director?

498
00:29:55,152 --> 00:29:56,237
Let her call it?

499
00:29:56,279 --> 00:29:57,406
Or...

500
00:29:58,116 --> 00:30:00,370
maybe it's for--
for the Times or the Post.

501
00:30:00,412 --> 00:30:01,874
You've been
to the press with this?

502
00:30:01,915 --> 00:30:03,251
MOORE: You'll go to jail, idiot.

503
00:30:03,293 --> 00:30:06,049
Maybe.
But we'll all be there together.

504
00:30:06,090 --> 00:30:07,927
-We have a mission here.
-Uh-huh.

505
00:30:07,969 --> 00:30:09,388
A responsibility.

506
00:30:09,680 --> 00:30:12,603
We'll defend our nation
by any means necessary.

507
00:30:13,021 --> 00:30:14,816
I don't think
Mr. Heller came here

508
00:30:14,858 --> 00:30:18,031
to debate ethics
and practices, right?

509
00:30:18,073 --> 00:30:18,991
Right.

510
00:30:21,329 --> 00:30:23,793
First, you need to know that
I've set up a dead man's switch.

511
00:30:23,834 --> 00:30:25,546
If I don't code in
every five hours,

512
00:30:25,588 --> 00:30:27,592
these files will
automatically be sent

513
00:30:27,634 --> 00:30:29,971
to three top
investigative journalists,

514
00:30:30,013 --> 00:30:32,644
along with a detailed report
and timeline of the events.

515
00:30:32,686 --> 00:30:34,271
Twenty-four hours later,

516
00:30:34,314 --> 00:30:36,318
the files will be
released to the public.

517
00:30:36,360 --> 00:30:37,737
I get it.

518
00:30:37,779 --> 00:30:40,243
We kill you,
Wolf Blitzer wins an Emmy.

519
00:30:40,284 --> 00:30:41,119
No. Not just kill me.

520
00:30:41,160 --> 00:30:42,455
You put me in jail,

521
00:30:42,497 --> 00:30:44,376
you black-site me,
you extradite me...

522
00:30:44,418 --> 00:30:46,045
you'll only condemn yourselves.

523
00:30:46,088 --> 00:30:47,882
Then what the hell do you want?

524
00:30:47,924 --> 00:30:50,011
He wants us to kill the people
who killed his wife.

525
00:30:50,054 --> 00:30:51,473
No. No.

526
00:30:52,559 --> 00:30:53,936
I don't want you to kill them.

527
00:30:56,150 --> 00:30:57,987
I wanna kill them myself.

528
00:30:58,738 --> 00:30:59,740
(STIFLED LAUGH)

529
00:31:01,076 --> 00:31:02,872
-I beg your pardon?
-You heard me.

530
00:31:03,581 --> 00:31:05,460
I want to find and kill
the people who murdered my wife.

531
00:31:05,501 --> 00:31:07,505
(LAUGHS)

532
00:31:07,547 --> 00:31:08,632
The CIA will train me.

533
00:31:08,674 --> 00:31:10,595
(LAUGHS)

534
00:31:10,636 --> 00:31:13,559
I mean, this is
a practical joke, right?

535
00:31:13,601 --> 00:31:15,731
I don't think you could beat
a 90-year-old nun

536
00:31:15,773 --> 00:31:17,108
in an arm-wrestling match.

537
00:31:17,150 --> 00:31:18,319
-(LAUGHS)
-That's funny.

538
00:31:19,362 --> 00:31:20,448
Humor?

539
00:31:21,283 --> 00:31:23,078
I want
mission-specific training

540
00:31:23,120 --> 00:31:25,667
and all the information
the company has on these people.

541
00:31:25,709 --> 00:31:27,671
Cash. And a new identity.
A legend.

542
00:31:29,132 --> 00:31:31,387
-Anything else?
-(CALEB LAUGHING)

543
00:31:31,429 --> 00:31:33,182
An Aston Martin?

544
00:31:33,642 --> 00:31:35,186
A jet pack, maybe?

545
00:31:35,229 --> 00:31:36,481
(LAUGHS)

546
00:31:38,108 --> 00:31:39,654
I want a fighting chance.

547
00:31:41,241 --> 00:31:43,119
(HORNS HONKING)

548
00:31:48,088 --> 00:31:49,715
(DISTANT CHATTER)

549
00:31:54,725 --> 00:31:56,145
(EXHALES)

550
00:31:56,187 --> 00:31:57,398
(SNIFFS)

551
00:32:09,631 --> 00:32:11,342
How do we know he really set up
the dead man's switch?

552
00:32:11,384 --> 00:32:12,596
We don't.

553
00:32:12,637 --> 00:32:14,390
We need to keep a lid on this.

554
00:32:14,432 --> 00:32:15,434
Right.

555
00:32:16,812 --> 00:32:17,898
So, let's play along...

556
00:32:19,233 --> 00:32:20,402
till we're sure.

557
00:32:21,947 --> 00:32:23,868
What? Actually train him?

558
00:32:23,910 --> 00:32:25,455
What harm can it do?

559
00:32:25,496 --> 00:32:27,626
Probably quit of his own accord.

560
00:32:27,667 --> 00:32:29,588
Meanwhile, get Park onto him.

561
00:32:29,963 --> 00:32:31,634
I can't believe I'm doing this.

562
00:32:31,675 --> 00:32:35,475
We scrub his life
till we find the switch.

563
00:32:35,516 --> 00:32:36,977
If it exists.

564
00:32:37,019 --> 00:32:38,731
If it doesn't...

565
00:32:38,773 --> 00:32:41,445
well, maybe there's
a training accident.

566
00:32:41,946 --> 00:32:44,201
(INHALES DEEPLY)

567
00:32:44,242 --> 00:32:46,038
Let's use Henderson.

568
00:32:46,914 --> 00:32:48,834
WOMAN: Escort team, stand by
for new arrival at gate four.

569
00:32:50,838 --> 00:32:53,052
(HELICOPTERS WHIRRING OVERHEAD)

570
00:32:54,471 --> 00:32:55,348
MAN: Charles Heller?

571
00:32:56,600 --> 00:32:57,352
Charlie.

572
00:32:58,312 --> 00:32:59,314
You're late.

573
00:33:01,820 --> 00:33:03,322
With respect,
I'm actually about--

574
00:33:03,364 --> 00:33:04,701
You're late.

575
00:33:06,746 --> 00:33:07,665
You comin'?

576
00:33:14,595 --> 00:33:15,514
The hell you doin'?

577
00:33:16,432 --> 00:33:17,518
I'm not an Uber driver.

578
00:33:18,310 --> 00:33:19,229
Sorry.

579
00:33:24,407 --> 00:33:25,743
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

580
00:33:25,784 --> 00:33:27,413
-Okay.
-Put it over here on the left.

581
00:33:28,080 --> 00:33:28,999
MAN: Yeah. Put those
two routers over there.

582
00:33:29,041 --> 00:33:30,335
WOMAN: I got 'em.

583
00:33:30,377 --> 00:33:31,379
MAN: The HDMI cables
are in the box.

584
00:33:31,421 --> 00:33:33,090
PARK: My bet is he's bluffing.

585
00:33:33,132 --> 00:33:36,139
CALEB: The man has an IQ of 170.
Let's not assume.

586
00:33:36,765 --> 00:33:38,560
PARK: The only way out
is through security...

587
00:33:38,602 --> 00:33:40,773
and there's not a chance he got
past them with a digital file.

588
00:33:42,526 --> 00:33:45,074
Then why is he standing in
blind spots for over 40 minutes?

589
00:33:45,115 --> 00:33:47,119
Here, here, and here.
On this day.

590
00:33:50,375 --> 00:33:52,797
And look at that sweat.

591
00:33:52,839 --> 00:33:55,970
PARK:
Yeah. That is a lot of sweat.

592
00:34:00,521 --> 00:34:01,481
Are you my...

593
00:34:02,566 --> 00:34:03,527
...handler?

594
00:34:04,445 --> 00:34:05,865
I am Colonel Henderson.

595
00:34:06,951 --> 00:34:08,621
My friends call me Hendo.

596
00:34:08,663 --> 00:34:11,209
You will call me
Colonel Henderson.

597
00:34:12,044 --> 00:34:14,423
I have been asked to give you
a refresher course,

598
00:34:14,466 --> 00:34:16,052
even though
what you'll learn here

599
00:34:16,094 --> 00:34:18,306
is outside
the normal curriculum.

600
00:34:18,348 --> 00:34:19,768
Next to God Almighty,

601
00:34:19,810 --> 00:34:21,522
I am the most important
person in the world

602
00:34:21,564 --> 00:34:23,901
to an operative looking
to target enemy combatants.

603
00:34:23,943 --> 00:34:25,488
Do precisely as I say...

604
00:34:26,030 --> 00:34:28,828
and there is a slight chance
you may come out of this alive.

605
00:34:29,621 --> 00:34:30,665
(CHARLIE CHUCKLES)

606
00:34:31,834 --> 00:34:33,588
O-Only a slight chance?

607
00:34:33,629 --> 00:34:35,925
I'm overestimating your odds
to boost your confidence, son.

608
00:34:39,141 --> 00:34:42,230
Ladies and gentlemen,
please give us the room.

609
00:34:43,065 --> 00:34:45,278
Go have coffee. Now.

610
00:34:45,320 --> 00:34:47,199
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER)

611
00:34:51,958 --> 00:34:53,502
MAN: Yeah, make sure
you check for all spots.

612
00:34:53,544 --> 00:34:54,839
MAN 2: All right, checking.

613
00:34:55,673 --> 00:34:58,512
(ITEMS CLATTERING
AND CLANKING)

614
00:34:58,554 --> 00:34:59,849
MAN:
Open all hard drive cleaners.

615
00:35:01,101 --> 00:35:02,562
Bring the mountings too.

616
00:35:02,605 --> 00:35:04,024
Wait. You think
he used a skimmer?

617
00:35:04,066 --> 00:35:05,736
They don't work on these drives.

618
00:35:06,320 --> 00:35:08,241
TECH: They work on printers.

619
00:35:09,368 --> 00:35:11,413
Six days ago, he sent
the files to the printer...

620
00:35:11,456 --> 00:35:13,460
and skimmed them
with a magnetic strip...

621
00:35:14,044 --> 00:35:15,839
rewrote the software
in the printer.

622
00:35:16,298 --> 00:35:18,219
Doesn't mean he got
the strip out of the building.

623
00:35:19,555 --> 00:35:24,691
Okay. So, ANPR has his Saab at
Best Buy at 09:17 on the 13th,

624
00:35:24,732 --> 00:35:26,403
where he bought
the magnetic strip.

625
00:35:26,444 --> 00:35:27,530
Then got gas.

626
00:35:27,571 --> 00:35:30,034
Copied the files at 11:03...

627
00:35:30,076 --> 00:35:32,206
met you two the next morning.

628
00:35:32,248 --> 00:35:36,464
If he smuggled it out,
he did it here.

629
00:35:36,506 --> 00:35:38,427
Still, screener
picked up nothing.

630
00:35:38,468 --> 00:35:39,762
Maybe he swallowed it.

631
00:35:40,014 --> 00:35:41,308
PARK:
Still would have picked it up.

632
00:35:42,768 --> 00:35:44,731
(GUNSHOT ECHOES)

633
00:35:45,607 --> 00:35:47,528
(GUNFIRE)

634
00:35:54,793 --> 00:35:55,754
Kind of far.

635
00:35:56,463 --> 00:35:58,175
(GUNFIRE)

636
00:35:58,592 --> 00:35:59,636
You stand right there.

637
00:36:09,030 --> 00:36:10,825
-Hold your fire!
-(GUNFIRE STOPS)

638
00:36:10,867 --> 00:36:12,328
Try it closer.

639
00:36:12,371 --> 00:36:13,498
Just a few rounds.

640
00:36:24,102 --> 00:36:25,814
Jesus, Mary, and Joseph.

641
00:36:25,855 --> 00:36:27,192
Did we test your vision?

642
00:36:42,347 --> 00:36:44,059
Guess I just have
to get that close.

643
00:36:44,643 --> 00:36:46,605
Yeah, at point blank range...

644
00:36:47,482 --> 00:36:49,821
you might have a 50-50 chance
of hittin' something.

645
00:36:50,488 --> 00:36:52,451
Overestimating my odds?

646
00:36:56,417 --> 00:36:58,296
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

647
00:37:02,220 --> 00:37:04,141
MAN: Why don't you guys check
the downstairs bathroom?

648
00:37:04,183 --> 00:37:05,310
MAN 2: Pass me those boxes.

649
00:37:05,351 --> 00:37:06,228
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER)

650
00:37:09,903 --> 00:37:12,366
So, an IED consists
of an initiator...

651
00:37:13,201 --> 00:37:15,163
switch, main charge,

652
00:37:15,205 --> 00:37:17,502
power source,
container for enhancements.

653
00:37:17,543 --> 00:37:19,547
Stuff like fertilizer, nails,

654
00:37:19,589 --> 00:37:21,968
glass, ammonia nitrate.

655
00:37:22,010 --> 00:37:23,805
Beauty is,
you can use what you find,

656
00:37:23,847 --> 00:37:25,476
big or small, as you like.

657
00:37:25,518 --> 00:37:27,396
Improvise.
Design it for your purpose.

658
00:37:27,688 --> 00:37:29,275
Carry the components with you.

659
00:37:30,486 --> 00:37:32,323
HENDERSON: I'll be damned.

660
00:37:32,365 --> 00:37:34,536
Looks like we finally found
something you do well, Heller.

661
00:37:41,299 --> 00:37:42,468
May I keep this?

662
00:37:43,387 --> 00:37:44,890
Sure.

663
00:37:44,932 --> 00:37:47,228
He went here twice. This bar.

664
00:37:47,270 --> 00:37:48,815
Why?

665
00:37:48,856 --> 00:37:51,862
Once with Mr. Dominguez
on the night of the 24th.

666
00:37:51,904 --> 00:37:53,574
Couple of weeks
after his wife died.

667
00:37:53,616 --> 00:37:55,452
And then again,
the next month, the 13th.

668
00:37:55,494 --> 00:37:56,747
The day he downloaded the files.

669
00:37:56,789 --> 00:37:57,916
Right.

670
00:37:57,958 --> 00:37:59,377
We searched it, though.

671
00:37:59,419 --> 00:38:00,254
Let's search it again.

672
00:38:00,296 --> 00:38:01,381
HENDERSON: Name?

673
00:38:01,423 --> 00:38:02,383
CHARLIE: Clark Nicholas Jenson.

674
00:38:02,426 --> 00:38:03,469
Spell that for me.

675
00:38:03,511 --> 00:38:05,139
(STAMMERS) J-E-N-S-O-N.

676
00:38:05,180 --> 00:38:06,057
-You sure?
-Yeah.

677
00:38:06,099 --> 00:38:07,268
Not Jenson Clark?

678
00:38:07,310 --> 00:38:08,771
-No!
-Fast.

679
00:38:08,813 --> 00:38:10,525
-Clark Nicholas Jenson.
-Where were you born?

680
00:38:10,567 --> 00:38:12,111
Raleigh.
Raleigh, North Carolina.

681
00:38:12,153 --> 00:38:14,366
-Which hospital? Now!
-Uh, Duke University Hospital.

682
00:38:14,408 --> 00:38:16,621
-Your mother's maiden name?
-Uh, Deborah Jane Hammock.

683
00:38:16,662 --> 00:38:17,456
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS)

684
00:38:19,668 --> 00:38:20,420
Just a sec.

685
00:38:24,136 --> 00:38:26,057
(PRINTER BEEPING AND WHIRRING)

686
00:38:27,934 --> 00:38:30,190
It's all being re-swept.
Even the parking lot.

687
00:38:30,231 --> 00:38:31,692
There's no drive here.

688
00:38:31,943 --> 00:38:33,571
Okay. That's what
we didn't find.

689
00:38:33,613 --> 00:38:35,241
But what did we find?

690
00:38:36,243 --> 00:38:39,333
I don't know, this was
stuck under the jukebox.

691
00:38:43,466 --> 00:38:44,803
Give me a quarter.

692
00:38:50,731 --> 00:38:52,359
(JUKEBOX WHIRRING)

693
00:38:56,785 --> 00:38:58,539
(ELECTRONIC BLIPS AND STATIC)

694
00:38:58,580 --> 00:38:59,541
Pull the disc.

695
00:39:03,005 --> 00:39:04,258
(DOOR THUDS OPEN)

696
00:39:04,884 --> 00:39:06,011
(SIGHS)

697
00:39:08,809 --> 00:39:09,811
You...

698
00:39:10,771 --> 00:39:11,773
are not a killer.

699
00:39:13,986 --> 00:39:14,988
No?

700
00:39:15,281 --> 00:39:17,118
-Hey, who's this?
-Leave them.

701
00:39:18,035 --> 00:39:19,622
Oh, these the assholes
that killed your wife, huh?

702
00:39:21,376 --> 00:39:24,340
So, how do you plan
to take them all out?

703
00:39:24,382 --> 00:39:25,760
The first one you kill,

704
00:39:25,801 --> 00:39:27,096
you let the other ones
know you're coming.

705
00:39:27,138 --> 00:39:28,640
And then what? What's your plan?

706
00:39:28,891 --> 00:39:30,060
How are you gonna keep

707
00:39:30,102 --> 00:39:31,188
the people
at Langley off your ass?

708
00:39:32,983 --> 00:39:34,611
That's what I need
you to teach me.

709
00:39:34,652 --> 00:39:36,198
(SCOFFS)

710
00:39:36,239 --> 00:39:37,283
All right. I'll teach you.

711
00:39:40,664 --> 00:39:41,918
Take it.

712
00:39:41,959 --> 00:39:42,878
-Oh, come on.
-Go on, take it.

713
00:39:42,920 --> 00:39:43,797
What is it? What are you...

714
00:39:43,838 --> 00:39:45,049
-Take it! Now!
-Hey!

715
00:39:47,386 --> 00:39:48,555
Point it at my chest.

716
00:39:49,558 --> 00:39:50,852
-Point it at my chest!
-You think that...

717
00:39:50,894 --> 00:39:53,357
-Do it now!
-All right, all right.

718
00:39:53,398 --> 00:39:55,110
-Put your finger on the trigger!
-(EXHALES NERVOUSLY)

719
00:39:56,948 --> 00:39:58,325
Come on.

720
00:39:58,367 --> 00:39:59,285
Look at me.

721
00:40:00,997 --> 00:40:02,835
(BREATHES SHAKILY)

722
00:40:03,586 --> 00:40:04,672
Come on.

723
00:40:05,465 --> 00:40:07,093
-Come on, Charlie.
-(CHARLIE EXHALES SHAKILY)

724
00:40:18,157 --> 00:40:19,326
Paralyzing, isn't it?

725
00:40:20,036 --> 00:40:21,497
(GUN CLICKS)

726
00:40:21,539 --> 00:40:23,126
Pointing a live weapon
at someone like that.

727
00:40:26,090 --> 00:40:28,469
You have to either be
very confident or very stupid,

728
00:40:28,511 --> 00:40:30,724
which is its own
kind of confidence.

729
00:40:30,975 --> 00:40:32,979
Truth is you don't have
that kinda confidence.

730
00:40:33,021 --> 00:40:35,818
And you are not stupid.
Not in the slightest.

731
00:40:35,860 --> 00:40:37,279
You're just not a killer,
Charlie.

732
00:40:38,824 --> 00:40:40,076
People have certain gifts.

733
00:40:41,830 --> 00:40:44,543
You can't do what I do, no
matter how much I train you...

734
00:40:45,337 --> 00:40:48,384
as much as you can't teach me
how to break code.

735
00:40:48,426 --> 00:40:50,388
I can't make you into somethin'
that you're not.

736
00:40:51,098 --> 00:40:52,225
I'm sorry.

737
00:40:54,313 --> 00:40:55,691
When the time comes...

738
00:40:56,985 --> 00:40:58,572
I'll pull--
I'll pull the trigger.

739
00:40:58,614 --> 00:41:00,241
HENDERSON:
When the time comes...

740
00:41:00,493 --> 00:41:02,120
you won't even remember
which end of the gun

741
00:41:02,162 --> 00:41:03,457
the bullet comes out of.

742
00:41:08,132 --> 00:41:10,053
(COMPUTER BLIPS)

743
00:41:12,015 --> 00:41:13,143
MOORE:
How long is this gonna take?

744
00:41:14,813 --> 00:41:17,026
With this encryption,
four or five hours.

745
00:41:22,328 --> 00:41:24,666
CALEB: (OVER RADIO)
What if she can't break
Heller's encryption?

746
00:41:24,708 --> 00:41:25,877
MOORE: She will.

747
00:41:26,753 --> 00:41:28,799
CALEB: How do we know
he didn't make 50 copies?

748
00:41:29,426 --> 00:41:31,013
MOORE: We don't. (SIGHS)

749
00:41:34,185 --> 00:41:35,772
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

750
00:41:37,483 --> 00:41:38,485
CALEB: Ali.

751
00:41:38,527 --> 00:41:39,655
PARK: We're in.

752
00:41:39,697 --> 00:41:40,991
It's a bluff.

753
00:41:41,241 --> 00:41:42,661
He was playing us.

754
00:41:42,703 --> 00:41:44,164
CALEB:
And he did pretty well, too.

755
00:41:45,584 --> 00:41:46,460
Take him off the board?

756
00:41:48,213 --> 00:41:50,092
(CELL PHONE VIBRATES)

757
00:41:52,096 --> 00:41:53,975
(GRUNTS AND SNIFFS)

758
00:41:55,854 --> 00:41:56,773
Yeah.

759
00:42:03,870 --> 00:42:04,747
Okay.

760
00:42:20,320 --> 00:42:21,864
He's gone?

761
00:42:21,907 --> 00:42:23,284
HENDERSON: He's got a bag
full of passports.

762
00:42:23,326 --> 00:42:25,122
Even hacked the biometrics.

763
00:42:25,163 --> 00:42:26,624
Yeah, he got out
on a janitor's card.

764
00:42:26,666 --> 00:42:28,211
MOORE: This is a joke.

765
00:42:28,796 --> 00:42:30,382
Maybe y'all misjudged
this individual.

766
00:42:30,423 --> 00:42:31,217
MOORE: You think?

767
00:42:34,683 --> 00:42:36,937
He knew exactly
what he was doin'.

768
00:42:37,772 --> 00:42:40,110
Kept us chasin' breadcrumbs
just long enough...

769
00:42:40,570 --> 00:42:42,114
while he got himself
some training.

770
00:42:43,408 --> 00:42:44,911
(EXHALES)

771
00:43:14,137 --> 00:43:15,640
(SIGHS)

772
00:43:17,769 --> 00:43:18,729
Mr. Heller...

773
00:43:20,733 --> 00:43:22,905
bugging a CIA officer...

774
00:43:23,322 --> 00:43:25,117
is treason.

775
00:43:25,159 --> 00:43:28,792
ANNOUNCER: Call for flight
AA143 to London Heathrow.

776
00:43:32,716 --> 00:43:34,094
(JET ENGINE ROARING)

777
00:43:37,517 --> 00:43:39,271
FLIGHT ATTENDANT: Ladies
and gentlemen, welcome aboard

778
00:43:39,312 --> 00:43:42,277
American Airlines flight AA143,

779
00:43:42,318 --> 00:43:43,822
with service
from Washington Dulles

780
00:43:43,863 --> 00:43:45,575
to London Heathrow.

781
00:43:46,285 --> 00:43:48,540
We thank you for your attention
whilst we demonstrate

782
00:43:48,581 --> 00:43:51,086
the safety features
of the aircraft.

783
00:43:53,341 --> 00:43:54,635
(BOTH LAUGH)

784
00:43:55,929 --> 00:43:57,015
Yes?

785
00:43:57,056 --> 00:43:58,810
Okay, you can open them.

786
00:44:00,814 --> 00:44:02,276
(EXHALES)

787
00:44:03,528 --> 00:44:04,947
Happy birthday.

788
00:44:07,536 --> 00:44:08,580
(GASPS)

789
00:44:10,375 --> 00:44:11,794
CHARLIE: Did it-- did it crash?

790
00:44:11,836 --> 00:44:14,091
Apparently it wasn't
tied down properly

791
00:44:14,133 --> 00:44:16,471
and got thrown around
in a tornado

792
00:44:16,512 --> 00:44:18,308
or hurricane or something.

793
00:44:18,350 --> 00:44:20,312
(CHARLIE LAUGHS)

794
00:44:20,354 --> 00:44:21,230
SARAH: What do you think?

795
00:44:22,441 --> 00:44:24,612
CHARLIE: I have no words.

796
00:44:25,489 --> 00:44:27,242
-SARAH: Yeah?
-CHARLIE: Yeah.

797
00:44:27,284 --> 00:44:28,328
SARAH: It's not crazy?

798
00:44:33,213 --> 00:44:34,674
It needs some work.

799
00:44:36,260 --> 00:44:37,096
CHARLIE: You think?

800
00:44:42,147 --> 00:44:43,274
This...

801
00:44:44,110 --> 00:44:46,365
This is the most beautiful thing
I've ever seen.

802
00:44:47,742 --> 00:44:48,869
Yeah?

803
00:44:48,911 --> 00:44:50,122
Yeah.

804
00:44:51,207 --> 00:44:52,460
Second most.

805
00:44:56,050 --> 00:44:57,010
Happy birthday.

806
00:45:01,060 --> 00:45:03,107
(INDISTINCT ANNOUNCEMENT)

807
00:45:03,149 --> 00:45:05,820
...Paris will be departing now
from platform two.

808
00:45:09,453 --> 00:45:11,206
-(OVERLAPPING CHATTER)
-(TELEPHONES RINGING)

809
00:45:14,754 --> 00:45:16,216
He's in London.

810
00:45:16,258 --> 00:45:17,928
One of his passports
just lit up at immigration

811
00:45:17,970 --> 00:45:19,932
on his way to Paris.

812
00:45:19,974 --> 00:45:22,145
-I'll grab local liaison.
-No.

813
00:45:22,187 --> 00:45:23,522
This stays with us.

814
00:45:24,399 --> 00:45:25,401
What about Henderson?

815
00:45:27,405 --> 00:45:28,783
Call him.

816
00:45:34,252 --> 00:45:35,338
(CAR HORN HONKING)

817
00:45:38,385 --> 00:45:40,264
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

818
00:45:47,613 --> 00:45:49,492
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

819
00:45:54,125 --> 00:45:56,004
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER)

820
00:45:59,095 --> 00:46:01,224
(BELLS JINGLE)

821
00:46:08,029 --> 00:46:09,824
(DISTANT SIREN WAILING)

822
00:46:16,755 --> 00:46:18,174
Non, vraiment,
vous êtes déjà fermés?

823
00:46:30,992 --> 00:46:32,411
(COMPUTER BEEPING)

824
00:46:33,371 --> 00:46:34,248
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

825
00:46:42,557 --> 00:46:44,436
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER)

826
00:46:56,418 --> 00:46:58,047
(DISTANT CHATTER)

827
00:47:02,472 --> 00:47:03,557
(DOOR CLOSES)

828
00:47:05,728 --> 00:47:07,190
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

829
00:47:11,031 --> 00:47:13,829
(DISTANT SIREN WAILING)

830
00:47:15,874 --> 00:47:17,168
(PASSERSBY SPEAKING FRENCH)

831
00:47:17,210 --> 00:47:18,379
(HORN HONKS)

832
00:47:24,182 --> 00:47:25,309
-(KEYPAD BEEPS)
-(DOOR BUZZES)

833
00:47:34,495 --> 00:47:37,208
(PANTING)

834
00:47:41,843 --> 00:47:43,388
MAN ON VIDEO:
Hey, there, lockpick fans.

835
00:47:43,430 --> 00:47:46,561
Okay. Today we're gonna pick
an apartment-style lock.

836
00:47:46,603 --> 00:47:48,356
So, the first thing
we're gonna do

837
00:47:48,398 --> 00:47:49,817
is you're gonna take
your tension wrench

838
00:47:49,859 --> 00:47:51,446
and you're gonna
stick it in the bottom

839
00:47:51,488 --> 00:47:53,116
of the keyhole and the plug...

840
00:47:53,158 --> 00:47:54,869
just like so. Feel it?

841
00:47:54,911 --> 00:47:56,456
-(DISTANT DOOR OPENS)
-(DISTANT CHATTER)

842
00:47:56,498 --> 00:47:57,708
You're gonna apply just
a little bit of pressure,

843
00:47:57,750 --> 00:47:59,462
just a little bit.

844
00:47:59,504 --> 00:48:00,924
-Hey, you don't want too much.
-(CHATTER GROWS NEARER)

845
00:48:00,965 --> 00:48:02,343
MAN ON VIDEO: Too much,
and what's gonna happen

846
00:48:02,384 --> 00:48:04,055
is the pins are gonna
bind up on you...

847
00:48:04,096 --> 00:48:06,226
and you won't be able
to get 'em up on a shear line.

848
00:48:06,267 --> 00:48:08,772
And you're not gonna
get into that door.

849
00:48:08,815 --> 00:48:12,613
So, gently, gently...

850
00:48:12,655 --> 00:48:16,454
and feel it rotate back and
forwards, listening carefully.

851
00:48:16,496 --> 00:48:18,124
Just a light touch.

852
00:48:18,166 --> 00:48:21,130
All the pins are gonna line up.

853
00:48:21,172 --> 00:48:24,345
And then, you're in.
There you go.

854
00:48:24,387 --> 00:48:25,515
How to pick a lock.
(CHUCKLES)

855
00:48:25,557 --> 00:48:26,851
Pretty darn easy.

856
00:48:27,268 --> 00:48:29,146
Um... Yeah, don't forget
to like and subscribe.

857
00:48:29,188 --> 00:48:30,315
Thank y'all. See you next week.

858
00:48:32,571 --> 00:48:34,449
(HINGES CREAKING)

859
00:48:48,144 --> 00:48:50,064
(FLOOR CREAKS)

860
00:49:00,084 --> 00:49:02,547
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)

861
00:49:21,628 --> 00:49:24,091
(CELL PHONE BLIPPING)

862
00:49:24,132 --> 00:49:24,884
(GASPS)

863
00:49:30,311 --> 00:49:32,190
(EXHALES)

864
00:49:32,232 --> 00:49:35,113
GRETCHEN: Moi, j'oublie tout.
Bon, je te prête mes talons...

865
00:49:39,205 --> 00:49:40,123
(GASPS)

866
00:49:41,668 --> 00:49:43,964
(DISTANT CHATTER)

867
00:49:45,259 --> 00:49:48,432
MAN: T'as oublié le pain.

868
00:49:49,350 --> 00:49:51,438
GRETCHEN: La boulangerie était
fermée, tu te fiches de moi.

869
00:49:52,231 --> 00:49:53,692
Tu veux mes talons
pour aller plus vite
ou comment ça se passe?

870
00:49:59,579 --> 00:50:01,876
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

871
00:50:01,917 --> 00:50:03,045
(GRETCHEN SPEAKING FRENCH)

872
00:50:04,505 --> 00:50:05,466
(GRETCHEN LAUGHS)

873
00:50:07,344 --> 00:50:08,638
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

874
00:50:11,519 --> 00:50:13,691
(SPEECH GROWS DISTANT)

875
00:50:13,733 --> 00:50:15,069
(DOOR CLOSES)

876
00:50:15,110 --> 00:50:16,822
(GASPS AND EXHALES)

877
00:50:18,993 --> 00:50:20,872
(DISTANT CHATTER AND SIREN)

878
00:50:35,360 --> 00:50:37,322
(PANTING)

879
00:50:39,868 --> 00:50:40,829
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

880
00:50:40,870 --> 00:50:42,124
(GROANS)

881
00:50:45,003 --> 00:50:46,882
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

882
00:51:24,082 --> 00:51:25,336
(HEAVY EXHALE)

883
00:51:27,298 --> 00:51:29,134
(DISTANT SIREN WAILING)

884
00:51:43,455 --> 00:51:45,125
CHARLIE: Bonjour.
Parlez, uh, anglais?

885
00:51:45,167 --> 00:51:46,503
WOMAN: Um, yes.

886
00:51:47,505 --> 00:51:48,507
-Sunflowers.
-Yeah.

887
00:51:48,548 --> 00:51:49,300
Excuse me.

888
00:51:50,761 --> 00:51:51,721
All of them, please.

889
00:51:52,765 --> 00:51:53,851
Tous?

890
00:51:53,893 --> 00:51:55,312
The lilies as well, please.

891
00:51:56,439 --> 00:51:57,525
I'll get all of them.

892
00:51:57,566 --> 00:51:59,947
(LAUGHS)

893
00:51:59,989 --> 00:52:02,368
You must have done
something really bad.

894
00:52:03,788 --> 00:52:04,748
Not yet.

895
00:52:18,233 --> 00:52:20,447
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

896
00:52:20,488 --> 00:52:22,033
WAITER:
Et voici votre café, madame.

897
00:52:22,074 --> 00:52:24,747
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER)

898
00:52:44,119 --> 00:52:46,332
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

899
00:52:52,845 --> 00:52:54,515
MAN: Ca fait treize
fois que j'vous appelle.

900
00:52:59,943 --> 00:53:02,114
-(MACHINES BEEPING)
-(COMPUTER BLIPS)

901
00:53:02,155 --> 00:53:03,241
(COMPUTER WHIRS)

902
00:53:03,282 --> 00:53:04,744
(TAPPING KEYBOARD HEAVILY)

903
00:53:07,834 --> 00:53:11,675
Mademoiselle Frank.
Je vous pris de m'excuser.
Continuez l'exercise.

904
00:53:16,768 --> 00:53:18,522
Qu'est-ce qui se passe?

905
00:53:18,564 --> 00:53:19,607
Je sais pas, Docteur,
y'a tout qui s'est éteint là...

906
00:53:19,649 --> 00:53:20,860
-Ca marche pas là-bas?
-Non.

907
00:53:20,901 --> 00:53:22,280
Mais attends, viens,
on va aller voir.

908
00:53:22,321 --> 00:53:24,116
-J'appelle IT?
-Oui, appelle IT.

909
00:53:32,133 --> 00:53:33,677
Excusez-moi,
le docteur Lessoir, il est ou?

910
00:53:35,639 --> 00:53:37,477
Vous faites quoi, là? Oh!

911
00:53:37,518 --> 00:53:39,939
Ouvrez la porte!
Ouvrez la porte!

912
00:53:40,608 --> 00:53:42,111
Ouvrez cette porte! Oh!

913
00:53:45,659 --> 00:53:46,954
-(AIR HISSES)
-GRETCHEN: Ouvrez cette porte!

914
00:53:46,996 --> 00:53:49,334
-(BANGING)
-(SHOUTING IN FRENCH)

915
00:53:50,294 --> 00:53:51,379
Ouvrez la porte!

916
00:53:51,421 --> 00:53:56,014
(WHEEZING)

917
00:53:56,556 --> 00:53:58,393
(COUGHING AND WHEEZING)

918
00:54:01,066 --> 00:54:01,901
C'est quoi ça?

919
00:54:01,943 --> 00:54:03,403
It's pollen.

920
00:54:03,445 --> 00:54:05,867
-(DOOR THUDS)
-DOCTOR: Mademoiselle Frank?

921
00:54:05,909 --> 00:54:07,996
-Who are you?
-Tell me where Horst Schiller is
and I'll let you out.

922
00:54:08,038 --> 00:54:09,792
Screw you.

923
00:54:09,833 --> 00:54:11,086
(AIR HISSES)

924
00:54:11,420 --> 00:54:12,171
No.

925
00:54:12,213 --> 00:54:13,550
No.

926
00:54:13,800 --> 00:54:15,345
-(YELLS AND WHEEZES)
-DOCTOR: Ouvrez la porte!

927
00:54:15,929 --> 00:54:17,349
Mademoiselle Frank!

928
00:54:17,391 --> 00:54:18,476
-(BANGING ON DOOR)
-GRETCHEN: No, no, no, no.

929
00:54:19,143 --> 00:54:21,022
DOCTOR: T'as appelé les flics?
Qu'est-ce que tu fais, Miriam?

930
00:54:21,064 --> 00:54:24,070
(WHEEZING)

931
00:54:24,488 --> 00:54:26,032
No, no, no.
That's not gonna work.

932
00:54:27,160 --> 00:54:28,663
Open the door.

933
00:54:28,705 --> 00:54:29,748
I'm sorry.
Not until you tell me.

934
00:54:29,790 --> 00:54:30,792
Please,
just tell me where he is.

935
00:54:30,834 --> 00:54:31,502
NURSE: Ouvrez la porte!

936
00:54:32,254 --> 00:54:33,423
Why?

937
00:54:34,049 --> 00:54:35,552
Because you killed my wife.

938
00:54:36,554 --> 00:54:38,057
Her name was Sarah.

939
00:54:39,351 --> 00:54:40,604
Tell me where he is.

940
00:54:40,645 --> 00:54:41,856
(BANGING ON DOOR)

941
00:54:41,898 --> 00:54:43,359
-Tell me!
-(WHEEZING AND WHIMPERING)

942
00:54:43,401 --> 00:54:44,612
Tell me!

943
00:54:44,653 --> 00:54:46,282
I don't... I don't know.

944
00:54:46,324 --> 00:54:47,701
-He contacts...
-(MUFFLED SHOUTING OUTSIDE)

945
00:54:48,620 --> 00:54:50,123
He contacts us.

946
00:54:50,165 --> 00:54:51,752
Messenger...
Messenger...

947
00:54:51,793 --> 00:54:52,879
I can't hear you.

948
00:54:52,920 --> 00:54:54,256
(MUFFLED SHOUTING CONTINUES)

949
00:54:54,298 --> 00:54:55,467
I can't hear you.

950
00:54:55,508 --> 00:54:56,552
Ouvrez la porte. Merde!

951
00:54:57,304 --> 00:54:58,389
Shit!

952
00:54:58,641 --> 00:55:00,561
(WHEEZING LOUDLY)

953
00:55:03,651 --> 00:55:05,070
-(LOCK CLICKS)
-(BEEPING)

954
00:55:05,111 --> 00:55:06,322
-(AIR HISSES)
-(GROWLS)

955
00:55:06,823 --> 00:55:07,909
(CHARLIE YELPS)

956
00:55:08,368 --> 00:55:11,917
(BOTH GRUNTING AND GASPING)

957
00:55:17,595 --> 00:55:19,599
(BOTH PANTING AND GROANING)

958
00:55:22,855 --> 00:55:26,113
(BOTH GRUNTING)

959
00:55:29,034 --> 00:55:30,496
(INDISTINCT SHOUTS)

960
00:55:33,419 --> 00:55:34,713
(BOTH STRAINING)

961
00:55:36,842 --> 00:55:39,097
(BOTH GRUNTING)

962
00:55:46,319 --> 00:55:48,198
(PANTING AND WHEEZING)

963
00:55:52,750 --> 00:55:55,212
(EXCITED CHATTER)

964
00:55:58,302 --> 00:56:00,014
-(CROWD SCREAMS)
-(TIRES SCREECH)

965
00:56:04,857 --> 00:56:07,488
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

966
00:56:10,952 --> 00:56:12,498
MAN: Appelez les secours!

967
00:56:18,635 --> 00:56:21,390
-(CAR HORNS HONKING)
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER CONTINUES)

968
00:56:23,645 --> 00:56:25,065
MAN: Arrêtez-le! Arrêtez-le!

969
00:56:25,106 --> 00:56:26,108
-Il lui a pris son téléphone!
-WOMAN: Madame?

970
00:56:26,150 --> 00:56:27,069
Madame, vous m'entendez?

971
00:56:27,110 --> 00:56:29,031
(RASPING BREATHS)

972
00:56:39,218 --> 00:56:41,430
(PANTING AND GRUNTING)

973
00:56:56,712 --> 00:56:57,755
Shit.

974
00:57:01,763 --> 00:57:03,308
Hello. Bonjour.

975
00:57:03,349 --> 00:57:05,312
-MAN: Hello.
-Marseille, s'il vous plaît.

976
00:57:05,688 --> 00:57:07,065
37 euros, please, sir.

977
00:57:43,305 --> 00:57:45,351
(AIR BRAKES HISS)

978
00:57:45,393 --> 00:57:48,900
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

979
00:57:50,152 --> 00:57:51,990
(CHURCH BELLS TOLLING FAINTLY)

980
00:57:55,037 --> 00:57:56,791
What do we know
about Gretchen Frank?

981
00:57:59,505 --> 00:58:02,176
Our people say one of her
own folks ran her down.

982
00:58:03,220 --> 00:58:05,892
Most likely fallout from
when the London job went south.

983
00:58:06,894 --> 00:58:08,398
I'll let State know.

984
00:58:08,440 --> 00:58:09,650
French ambassador is asking.

985
00:58:09,692 --> 00:58:10,652
Wasn't us.

986
00:58:15,119 --> 00:58:18,710
(LAUGHTER AND CHATTER)

987
00:58:18,752 --> 00:58:20,589
(MUFFLED DANCE MUSIC PLAYING)

988
00:58:26,517 --> 00:58:30,150
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER)

989
00:58:31,444 --> 00:58:34,826
(DANCE MUSIC CONTINUES, LOUDER)

990
00:58:46,182 --> 00:58:49,396
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

991
00:58:50,817 --> 00:58:52,904
(CROWD NOISES FADE)

992
00:58:56,119 --> 00:58:58,248
(MUFFLED VOICES ECHOING)

993
00:59:02,841 --> 00:59:05,263
(CROWD CHEERING, MUFFLED)

994
00:59:39,790 --> 00:59:42,503
(DANCE MUSIC CONTINUES, LOUDER)

995
00:59:56,240 --> 00:59:59,580
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER AND SHOUTS)

996
01:00:01,793 --> 01:00:03,672
WOMAN:
Mais fais attention, abruti!

997
01:00:03,713 --> 01:00:04,507
MAN: Hé, t'es fou!

998
01:00:08,723 --> 01:00:10,769
(PANTING AND GRUNTING)

999
01:00:17,283 --> 01:00:19,161
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1000
01:00:30,058 --> 01:00:33,148
(HIP-HOP MUSIC PLAYS)

1001
01:00:41,372 --> 01:00:45,088
(PANTING)

1002
01:01:08,677 --> 01:01:10,848
(PANTING)

1003
01:01:10,890 --> 01:01:14,439
(MUFFLED HIP-HOP MUSIC)

1004
01:01:14,481 --> 01:01:16,443
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1005
01:01:31,557 --> 01:01:32,559
You want a beer?

1006
01:01:35,314 --> 01:01:36,567
Yeah. Yeah, sure.

1007
01:01:36,609 --> 01:01:38,112
Deux Heineken, s'il vous plaît.

1008
01:01:43,247 --> 01:01:45,042
How did you find me?

1009
01:01:45,084 --> 01:01:47,673
Phone you pulled
off Gretchen Frank.

1010
01:01:48,215 --> 01:01:49,844
-It's like a radar ping.
-Shit.

1011
01:01:51,096 --> 01:01:52,600
Doesn't matter
how smart you are.

1012
01:01:52,641 --> 01:01:55,229
If you panic, that will
always screw up a good plan.

1013
01:02:04,332 --> 01:02:06,294
Then there's
the survival instinct.

1014
01:02:06,711 --> 01:02:08,131
No one goes down easy.

1015
01:02:09,467 --> 01:02:11,179
And, of course, the aftermath,

1016
01:02:11,221 --> 01:02:14,143
when you realize you've done
something you can't undo, ever.

1017
01:02:16,439 --> 01:02:17,316
I can live with that.

1018
01:02:18,693 --> 01:02:19,612
You can't.

1019
01:02:22,994 --> 01:02:24,121
You surprised me, Charlie.

1020
01:02:24,163 --> 01:02:26,125
I can't tell you
how rare that is.

1021
01:02:26,167 --> 01:02:28,213
But it ends here.

1022
01:02:29,841 --> 01:02:32,596
There are no three-volley
salutes in this work.

1023
01:02:33,431 --> 01:02:35,060
We're the John Does
that get found in the dumpster,

1024
01:02:35,102 --> 01:02:36,730
if we get found.

1025
01:02:36,772 --> 01:02:37,691
Which you won't.

1026
01:02:42,534 --> 01:02:43,619
I'm sorry.

1027
01:02:46,834 --> 01:02:48,295
No, those were good lessons.

1028
01:02:50,800 --> 01:02:52,512
You're a good teacher, Hendo.

1029
01:02:54,808 --> 01:02:56,353
I took that into account.

1030
01:02:58,399 --> 01:02:59,985
Fifty-fifty odds, right?

1031
01:03:01,655 --> 01:03:04,745
Did you ever account
for the things I was good at?

1032
01:03:06,915 --> 01:03:08,628
Base charge on a timer.

1033
01:03:09,338 --> 01:03:10,966
(EXPLOSION BOOMS)

1034
01:03:11,634 --> 01:03:14,222
(PANICKED SHOUTS AND CHATTER)

1035
01:03:16,143 --> 01:03:18,606
(ALARM BLARING)

1036
01:03:27,123 --> 01:03:30,213
(ALARM AND CHATTER CONTINUE)

1037
01:03:30,254 --> 01:03:33,553
(DISTANT BELL TOLLING)

1038
01:03:35,390 --> 01:03:37,310
(BIRDS CAWING)

1039
01:04:15,095 --> 01:04:17,224
ELECTRONIC VOICE:
You have one new message.

1040
01:04:17,266 --> 01:04:18,351
(BEEPS)

1041
01:04:18,811 --> 01:04:20,564
COMPUTERIZED VOICE:
Meet Ottoman Cargo.

1042
01:04:20,606 --> 01:04:22,986
Hangar seven.
They're expecting you.

1043
01:04:23,028 --> 01:04:25,282
You'll need 500 euros in cash.

1044
01:04:38,684 --> 01:04:40,522
ELECTRONIC VOICE:
You have one new message.

1045
01:04:40,563 --> 01:04:41,690
(BEEPS)

1046
01:04:42,526 --> 01:04:44,321
COMPUTERIZED VOICE:
The Fahri Cafe,
Kuveloglu Street.

1047
01:04:45,239 --> 01:04:46,575
I will pass you a book.

1048
01:04:52,587 --> 01:04:53,589
(DOOR SQUEAKS)

1049
01:05:01,063 --> 01:05:02,691
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1050
01:05:32,543 --> 01:05:33,377
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)

1051
01:05:42,103 --> 01:05:44,232
Wait. He is not
who you're looking for.

1052
01:05:46,404 --> 01:05:47,155
Check your phone.

1053
01:06:08,198 --> 01:06:09,910
It was reckless of you
to come here,

1054
01:06:09,952 --> 01:06:11,246
whatever your reasons.

1055
01:06:12,623 --> 01:06:13,835
Listen, I need your help.

1056
01:06:13,876 --> 01:06:16,214
No. You have nowhere else to go.

1057
01:06:16,256 --> 01:06:17,633
That's not the same thing.

1058
01:06:19,345 --> 01:06:21,016
We're shopping, okay?

1059
01:06:21,474 --> 01:06:22,476
Give me your backpack.

1060
01:06:23,311 --> 01:06:25,190
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1061
01:06:29,658 --> 01:06:30,702
And your hat.

1062
01:06:32,873 --> 01:06:34,418
Now you look less American.

1063
01:06:36,171 --> 01:06:37,298
What do you want?

1064
01:06:39,470 --> 01:06:40,847
My wife was murdered.

1065
01:06:40,889 --> 01:06:42,099
I know about your wife.

1066
01:06:44,396 --> 01:06:46,609
And Paris, that was you?

1067
01:06:48,738 --> 01:06:49,823
I need to find the others.

1068
01:06:49,865 --> 01:06:50,742
No. Not here.

1069
01:06:52,079 --> 01:06:53,623
There is a parking garage

1070
01:06:53,664 --> 01:06:55,085
four blocks
from here, that way.

1071
01:06:55,126 --> 01:06:56,796
First floor.

1072
01:06:56,837 --> 01:06:59,051
Do some shopping, then
meet me there in half an hour.

1073
01:06:59,093 --> 01:07:01,138
And if you're not followed,
we'll talk more.

1074
01:07:01,180 --> 01:07:04,394
WOMAN: Tabii. Evet. Aynen.

1075
01:07:25,103 --> 01:07:26,690
So, how long has it been you?

1076
01:07:27,775 --> 01:07:28,527
Six years.

1077
01:07:29,696 --> 01:07:31,825
My husband was a CIA asset.

1078
01:07:31,867 --> 01:07:33,495
Former KGB.

1079
01:07:33,537 --> 01:07:35,332
He was Inquiline until he died.

1080
01:07:37,295 --> 01:07:38,505
He fell out of a window.

1081
01:07:40,008 --> 01:07:41,219
I'm sorry.

1082
01:07:41,261 --> 01:07:42,722
Accidental falls from windows

1083
01:07:42,763 --> 01:07:45,144
are the number-one cause
of death of former KGB.

1084
01:07:45,186 --> 01:07:46,396
You didn't know?

1085
01:07:46,938 --> 01:07:48,942
He taught me
everything he was doing...

1086
01:07:48,984 --> 01:07:52,575
how to mine data cache,
encrypt files.

1087
01:07:54,037 --> 01:07:55,497
And after he died...

1088
01:07:55,873 --> 01:07:57,335
well, I decided to keep up
my connection

1089
01:07:57,376 --> 01:07:58,503
to your department...

1090
01:07:58,545 --> 01:08:00,216
in case I needed help.

1091
01:08:01,551 --> 01:08:03,848
Which is why I always thought
you were a middle-aged man.

1092
01:08:03,890 --> 01:08:05,601
Because you were, to begin with.

1093
01:08:07,396 --> 01:08:09,777
You aren't exactly
what I pictured, either.

1094
01:08:09,818 --> 01:08:11,446
How did you picture me?

1095
01:08:11,488 --> 01:08:12,448
I don't know.

1096
01:08:13,158 --> 01:08:15,329
Mr. CIA-man-with-a-gun, I guess.

1097
01:08:18,670 --> 01:08:19,838
So, you'll help me?

1098
01:08:25,140 --> 01:08:27,061
(BIRDS CAWING)

1099
01:08:41,549 --> 01:08:43,428
(TURKEYS CHITTERING)

1100
01:08:45,974 --> 01:08:47,686
It's better
than any alarm system.

1101
01:08:49,023 --> 01:08:51,819
(CHITTERING CONTINUES)

1102
01:08:52,738 --> 01:08:53,991
This is the first place

1103
01:08:54,033 --> 01:08:56,579
I've stayed in
for more than a month...

1104
01:08:56,620 --> 01:08:57,874
in the last three years.

1105
01:09:00,170 --> 01:09:01,589
I don't sleep.

1106
01:09:02,299 --> 01:09:04,720
But I just don't want
to run anymore.

1107
01:09:07,642 --> 01:09:09,480
What makes you think
they won't find you here?

1108
01:09:12,862 --> 01:09:14,156
For that night...

1109
01:09:14,699 --> 01:09:15,659
when they do.

1110
01:09:15,701 --> 01:09:16,787
You really think you're gonna

1111
01:09:16,828 --> 01:09:18,707
fight off
the Russians with that?

1112
01:09:18,749 --> 01:09:19,918
It's not for them.

1113
01:09:19,959 --> 01:09:21,170
It's for me.

1114
01:09:21,212 --> 01:09:23,091
(KEYBOARD CLICKING)

1115
01:09:25,053 --> 01:09:26,723
INQUILINE:
Those are the three, correct?

1116
01:09:26,765 --> 01:09:28,101
CHARLIE: Yeah.

1117
01:09:28,142 --> 01:09:30,063
Schiller seems
to be the coordinator.

1118
01:09:30,105 --> 01:09:31,817
Ringleader.

1119
01:09:31,858 --> 01:09:34,239
But he's also
the most difficult to profile.

1120
01:09:34,280 --> 01:09:35,825
As far as I can tell,

1121
01:09:35,866 --> 01:09:38,205
they operate as middlemen
in the proliferation chain.

1122
01:09:38,247 --> 01:09:39,958
And just like the data
you showed me...

1123
01:09:39,999 --> 01:09:43,382
they also source mercenaries
for Director Moore's black ops.

1124
01:09:43,424 --> 01:09:46,930
Ellish sources the weapons,
but he's beyond paranoid.

1125
01:09:46,972 --> 01:09:49,519
So, we have to find a way
to pull him out of the dark.

1126
01:09:50,020 --> 01:09:52,692
Okay. Perhaps I can
start the conversation.

1127
01:09:52,733 --> 01:09:54,612
Suggest I have
a contract for him.

1128
01:09:54,947 --> 01:09:56,491
See if he will engage.

1129
01:09:56,868 --> 01:09:59,122
CHARLIE: Okay.
And this is Mishka Blazhic.

1130
01:09:59,456 --> 01:10:01,126
He seems to be based in Moscow,

1131
01:10:01,168 --> 01:10:02,880
but he likes
to keep on the move.

1132
01:10:02,921 --> 01:10:06,303
Enjoys his luxuries.
Travels everywhere first class.

1133
01:10:06,553 --> 01:10:08,015
He may be the weak link.

1134
01:10:08,056 --> 01:10:09,559
Even posts online.

1135
01:10:09,894 --> 01:10:11,313
This was just last week.

1136
01:10:11,354 --> 01:10:14,904
No location, but
the vineyard on level ground...

1137
01:10:14,945 --> 01:10:17,074
and the spacing
is wider than typical,

1138
01:10:17,116 --> 01:10:19,078
so probably hotter climate.

1139
01:10:19,120 --> 01:10:21,249
Chalky soil. Maybe granite.

1140
01:10:21,291 --> 01:10:23,003
Low sun hitting
the wine in his glass.

1141
01:10:23,045 --> 01:10:25,425
But the vineyard
would be angled north-south...

1142
01:10:26,092 --> 01:10:27,513
so it's sunrise.

1143
01:10:28,180 --> 01:10:31,270
And this church.
The architecture looks Spanish.

1144
01:10:31,312 --> 01:10:32,481
So, hot in October.

1145
01:10:32,523 --> 01:10:34,235
Maybe central Spain.

1146
01:10:34,610 --> 01:10:35,946
And here, in the reflection...

1147
01:10:36,489 --> 01:10:37,699
girlfriend, maybe.

1148
01:10:37,741 --> 01:10:39,119
-(SIGHS)
-(KEYBOARD CLACKING)

1149
01:10:43,127 --> 01:10:44,296
INQUILINE: And there she is.

1150
01:10:46,300 --> 01:10:47,511
Alexandra Solovoya,

1151
01:10:48,388 --> 01:10:49,975
who also likes to travel.

1152
01:10:50,016 --> 01:10:53,106
And she flew Moscow
to Madrid, last week.

1153
01:10:53,899 --> 01:10:57,489
We need to project everything
that makes America great,

1154
01:10:57,531 --> 01:10:59,368
but we need to do it openly...

1155
01:10:59,410 --> 01:11:01,247
We have to assume
he's still alive.

1156
01:11:01,581 --> 01:11:02,583
He has three targets.

1157
01:11:02,624 --> 01:11:03,961
O'BRIEN: And so, I pledge...

1158
01:11:04,003 --> 01:11:06,717
We need to locate
and get eyes on all of them.

1159
01:11:06,758 --> 01:11:10,348
O'BRIEN: this agency will be
worthy of the nation's trust.

1160
01:11:10,390 --> 01:11:14,023
Within our country and beyond,
we will be accountable.

1161
01:11:14,524 --> 01:11:16,110
MOORE: I saw your speech.

1162
01:11:16,152 --> 01:11:17,279
It was excellent.

1163
01:11:18,156 --> 01:11:19,701
You know,
you're the first person

1164
01:11:19,743 --> 01:11:21,496
my predecessor briefed me on?

1165
01:11:22,122 --> 01:11:24,669
About the stick up your ass
on ISIS, AQ,

1166
01:11:24,711 --> 01:11:26,423
Iran, counterterrorism?

1167
01:11:27,550 --> 01:11:30,723
Even now, three years
after mandatory retirement,

1168
01:11:30,765 --> 01:11:32,059
they keep looking the other way.

1169
01:11:33,102 --> 01:11:35,441
But it's housekeeping time...

1170
01:11:35,983 --> 01:11:37,904
and I need to know
where you stand.

1171
01:11:38,614 --> 01:11:41,870
Sounds like you're suggesting
it's time for me to go private.

1172
01:11:41,912 --> 01:11:44,376
Write a neat book about my time
with the company.

1173
01:11:45,753 --> 01:11:48,384
Yet here we are,
enjoying this lovely meal.

1174
01:11:49,552 --> 01:11:50,721
So, why?

1175
01:11:50,763 --> 01:11:52,016
Oh, please.

1176
01:11:52,475 --> 01:11:54,020
I'm new, but I'm not stupid.

1177
01:11:55,231 --> 01:11:56,984
I need you to be accountable.

1178
01:11:57,652 --> 01:11:58,988
To me.

1179
01:11:59,572 --> 01:12:02,078
Stop playing
your black ops in the sand.

1180
01:12:02,370 --> 01:12:04,416
I need to be across everything.

1181
01:12:04,457 --> 01:12:06,086
And I mean everything.

1182
01:12:11,681 --> 01:12:12,933
Hey, Brian?

1183
01:12:13,601 --> 01:12:14,812
Can you bring me
another one of these

1184
01:12:14,854 --> 01:12:16,441
sourdough roll thingies?

1185
01:12:16,482 --> 01:12:17,316
Sure, Mr. Moore.

1186
01:12:19,321 --> 01:12:21,241
-I'll tell you a story.
-Mm.

1187
01:12:21,576 --> 01:12:26,627
Your predecessor sat me down
at this very same table,

1188
01:12:26,669 --> 01:12:29,216
no more than
a week into his term,

1189
01:12:29,258 --> 01:12:32,598
and gave me pretty much
this exact same speech.

1190
01:12:33,850 --> 01:12:34,935
Oh, wait.

1191
01:12:35,729 --> 01:12:37,691
Maybe it was his predecessor.

1192
01:12:37,733 --> 01:12:39,320
I can't remember.

1193
01:12:39,361 --> 01:12:42,034
Anyway, I'll tell you
what I told them.

1194
01:12:43,286 --> 01:12:44,580
You have my full support.

1195
01:12:48,254 --> 01:12:49,340
Good.

1196
01:12:50,675 --> 01:12:51,594
Good talk.

1197
01:12:54,976 --> 01:12:56,145
Enjoy that pasta.

1198
01:13:04,788 --> 01:13:06,082
Where?

1199
01:13:06,123 --> 01:13:07,167
Madrid.

1200
01:13:07,459 --> 01:13:08,587
On whose orders?

1201
01:13:08,629 --> 01:13:09,673
Your lunch date.

1202
01:13:14,724 --> 01:13:16,227
Let's get someone
of our own in play.

1203
01:13:23,409 --> 01:13:25,078
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1204
01:13:25,120 --> 01:13:26,373
INQUILINE: Found him.

1205
01:13:26,415 --> 01:13:28,168
At the Aguilar Hotel.

1206
01:13:28,210 --> 01:13:30,423
Five stars. Nightclub.
Rooftop pool.

1207
01:13:34,264 --> 01:13:35,349
What?

1208
01:13:36,143 --> 01:13:37,938
Langley will be onto him, too.

1209
01:13:38,898 --> 01:13:40,568
Well, then we
keep tracking him...

1210
01:13:40,818 --> 01:13:42,113
until we have a clear field.

1211
01:13:44,200 --> 01:13:46,246
(SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

1212
01:13:46,288 --> 01:13:47,707
CHARLIE: No.

1213
01:13:47,749 --> 01:13:49,044
I'm going.

1214
01:13:51,298 --> 01:13:52,258
Okay.

1215
01:13:54,179 --> 01:13:56,099
CHARLIE:
And keep an eye out for him.

1216
01:13:56,516 --> 01:13:57,770
This is who they'll send.

1217
01:14:03,615 --> 01:14:05,242
(ELEVATOR DINGS)

1218
01:14:05,284 --> 01:14:07,163
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1219
01:14:14,052 --> 01:14:15,722
(CHATTER AND LAUGHTER)

1220
01:14:15,764 --> 01:14:16,933
Cheers, cheers, cheers.

1221
01:14:16,975 --> 01:14:18,353
Nobody walks home.
We roll home.

1222
01:14:27,746 --> 01:14:29,542
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1223
01:14:30,627 --> 01:14:32,047
He's a night swimmer.

1224
01:14:32,923 --> 01:14:35,262
He pays the staff
to clear the rooftop for him.

1225
01:14:45,699 --> 01:14:47,202
MAN ON VIDEO:
...the approval of the team

1226
01:14:47,244 --> 01:14:49,791
and the ambitious plans
were given the green light.

1227
01:14:49,833 --> 01:14:52,546
The sky pool
is suspended 16 stories

1228
01:14:52,588 --> 01:14:54,341
above the ground,
which is 70 meters.

1229
01:14:54,718 --> 01:14:56,179
The thickness
of the clear glass

1230
01:14:56,220 --> 01:14:59,060
will be 420 centimeters
in total...

1231
01:14:59,101 --> 01:15:00,688
made of three panels
with air gaps

1232
01:15:00,730 --> 01:15:02,442
to improve the strength.

1233
01:15:02,484 --> 01:15:05,656
The pool will be three
meters tall, five meters wide,

1234
01:15:05,698 --> 01:15:09,581
and can hold an impressive
150 tons of water.

1235
01:15:11,250 --> 01:15:12,545
INQUILINE: (OVER PHONE)
You could shoot him from there.

1236
01:15:13,672 --> 01:15:15,133
You haven't seen me shoot.

1237
01:15:17,889 --> 01:15:20,353
Not for me to say here, boss,
but why bury him?

1238
01:15:20,394 --> 01:15:21,605
Why not just roll him up?

1239
01:15:21,647 --> 01:15:23,943
We're past that.
Too big of a stench.

1240
01:15:23,984 --> 01:15:26,406
Look, he practically invented
half of our surveillance tech.

1241
01:15:26,448 --> 01:15:28,160
Now, I will find him...

1242
01:15:28,786 --> 01:15:30,123
but you might have
a bigger stench on your hands

1243
01:15:30,164 --> 01:15:31,416
if he gives us the slip again.

1244
01:15:31,458 --> 01:15:32,962
You won't let that happen.

1245
01:15:37,595 --> 01:15:39,266
(WHISPERS) Charlie Heller.

1246
01:15:44,442 --> 01:15:47,574
-(WATER LAPPING)
-(CHATTER AND LAUGHTER)

1247
01:15:54,504 --> 01:15:56,551
Okay. You're going to
have to clue me in.

1248
01:15:56,843 --> 01:15:59,347
Integrity.
It's all about integrity.

1249
01:15:59,389 --> 01:16:01,477
To have morals,
something like that?

1250
01:16:01,519 --> 01:16:02,897
CHARLIE: Yeah.
And something else as well.

1251
01:16:03,147 --> 01:16:04,775
If I have the math right.

1252
01:16:05,485 --> 01:16:06,236
I should move.

1253
01:16:16,424 --> 01:16:18,595
-(AIR HISSING)
-(GENERATOR HUMMING)

1254
01:16:18,637 --> 01:16:22,269
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1255
01:16:30,702 --> 01:16:32,164
-Hola.
-¿Sí?

1256
01:16:32,206 --> 01:16:33,708
Can I confirm the pool
will be ready as usual?

1257
01:16:33,750 --> 01:16:35,003
CONCIERGE: Si, Señor.

1258
01:16:35,045 --> 01:16:35,922
-MISHKA: Gracias.
-CONCIERGE: De nada.

1259
01:16:40,639 --> 01:16:42,476
-Oh, my God.
-(CHATTER AND LAUGHTER)

1260
01:16:50,242 --> 01:16:52,371
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

1261
01:16:52,413 --> 01:16:53,206
MAN: Over here.

1262
01:16:54,083 --> 01:16:57,590
(DANCE MUSIC POUNDING)

1263
01:17:02,141 --> 01:17:03,769
Second stool down at the bar.

1264
01:17:04,396 --> 01:17:05,898
Yeah. What about him?

1265
01:17:05,940 --> 01:17:07,026
CHARLIE:
He's been following me.

1266
01:17:07,067 --> 01:17:08,821
I've clocked him three times.

1267
01:17:08,863 --> 01:17:10,908
Yeah, well, where there's one,
there's always more.

1268
01:17:15,335 --> 01:17:16,211
Shit.

1269
01:17:16,253 --> 01:17:17,255
You're right.

1270
01:17:17,547 --> 01:17:19,134
Yeah, I've got your man.

1271
01:17:19,176 --> 01:17:21,889
He's in the lobby, moving
across towards the elevators.

1272
01:17:22,891 --> 01:17:25,480
And the man at the bar,
I have an ID on him.

1273
01:17:26,065 --> 01:17:28,194
Charlie, he's also CIA.

1274
01:17:28,904 --> 01:17:30,406
You have to leave now.

1275
01:17:31,325 --> 01:17:32,577
Heller, are you listening
to me?

1276
01:17:34,414 --> 01:17:36,795
No. No, we go as planned.

1277
01:17:58,797 --> 01:18:00,299
(MISHKA SPEAKING SPANISH)

1278
01:18:07,105 --> 01:18:09,444
Tell me where
to find Horst Schiller.

1279
01:18:11,239 --> 01:18:12,241
Who are you?

1280
01:18:13,493 --> 01:18:15,456
You held a gun
to my wife's head.

1281
