01:34:02,490 --> 01:34:04,535
There's a café.
(SPEAKS RUSSIAN)

1537
01:34:05,788 --> 01:34:07,708
He calls in there,
and that's it.

1538
01:34:07,750 --> 01:34:08,960
How do you contact him?

1539
01:34:10,631 --> 01:34:13,010
He uses two numbers for his men.

1540
01:34:13,052 --> 01:34:14,764
If they get the right codes,
they know it's me.

1541
01:34:14,806 --> 01:34:16,518
That's all I have.

1542
01:34:16,559 --> 01:34:17,686
We'll see.

1543
01:34:17,728 --> 01:34:18,772
Give me your phone.

1544
01:34:19,022 --> 01:34:20,150
Your phone.

1545
01:34:22,070 --> 01:34:23,198
(CELL PHONE CLATTERS)

1546
01:34:27,832 --> 01:34:29,293
-(PHONE CLATTERS)
-The numbers are there.

1547
01:34:29,335 --> 01:34:30,546
The codes are by their names.

1548
01:34:37,184 --> 01:34:38,353
Their names?

1549
01:34:38,395 --> 01:34:40,691
Simon and Kristoff.

1550
01:34:40,732 --> 01:34:43,530
I'm not messing, man.
Simon and Kristoff. Come on.

1551
01:34:44,115 --> 01:34:46,035
-There. You see? See, I'm not...
-CHARLIE: You're right.

1552
01:34:46,077 --> 01:34:48,457
I'm not lying.
Now, deactivate this thing.

1553
01:34:51,171 --> 01:34:52,506
Hey, where are you going?

1554
01:34:53,008 --> 01:34:54,553
Where you going?

1555
01:34:54,595 --> 01:34:56,724
If you jump really fast,
you might survive the blast.

1556
01:34:56,765 --> 01:34:57,684
Please!

1557
01:34:58,561 --> 01:34:59,480
Wait!

1558
01:35:00,565 --> 01:35:01,484
Wait!

1559
01:35:09,291 --> 01:35:10,835
FEMALE AGENT:
We got a ping in Rome.

1560
01:35:10,877 --> 01:35:13,341
MOORE: The little prick
is now at a museum?

1561
01:35:13,382 --> 01:35:14,510
CALEB: He's not in Rome.

1562
01:35:15,386 --> 01:35:16,722
We're chasing vapors.

1563
01:35:16,764 --> 01:35:18,518
How?

1564
01:35:18,559 --> 01:35:21,273
Because they're shoveling what's
left of Mr. Lawrence Ellish

1565
01:35:21,315 --> 01:35:23,277
out of the mud in Romania.

1566
01:35:23,319 --> 01:35:24,571
TECH: He just got
on a tram in Prague.

1567
01:35:57,471 --> 01:35:58,724
(SEAGULLS CALLING)

1568
01:36:07,283 --> 01:36:08,869
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1569
01:36:22,772 --> 01:36:24,150
You need to sleep again.

1570
01:36:51,956 --> 01:36:55,797
-(MACHINES WHIRRING)
-(JACKHAMMER RATTLING)

1571
01:36:57,759 --> 01:37:01,350
(DISTANT SHOUTING)

1572
01:37:01,392 --> 01:37:06,067
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1573
01:37:10,952 --> 01:37:12,330
(HORN HONKS)

1574
01:37:19,219 --> 01:37:21,098
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1575
01:37:26,317 --> 01:37:28,654
(SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

1576
01:37:33,080 --> 01:37:34,208
(PHONE BLIPS)

1577
01:37:40,805 --> 01:37:42,767
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1578
01:37:54,624 --> 01:37:58,674
(INDISTINCT CHATTER CONTINUES)

1579
01:38:26,438 --> 01:38:28,860
(SPEAKS RUSSIAN)

1580
01:38:28,902 --> 01:38:30,487
Are you kidding me?

1581
01:38:30,529 --> 01:38:33,160
(CHUCKLES)
What do you think, man?

1582
01:38:33,201 --> 01:38:34,537
Just coincidence or what?

1583
01:38:34,579 --> 01:38:36,082
Yeah, somehow, I doubt that.

1584
01:38:36,667 --> 01:38:38,253
What do you say, maybe...

1585
01:38:38,295 --> 01:38:40,800
let's go get us a cup
of shitty Russian coffee, huh?

1586
01:38:40,842 --> 01:38:42,386
Come on.

1587
01:38:42,428 --> 01:38:43,681
Look at you
in the big, bad city.

1588
01:38:43,723 --> 01:38:44,934
Come on, let's go.

1589
01:38:46,102 --> 01:38:47,648
So, a rabbit on the run, huh?

1590
01:38:48,524 --> 01:38:52,532
(SPEAKS RUSSIAN)

1591
01:38:52,574 --> 01:38:54,536
(BOTH SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

1592
01:38:54,995 --> 01:38:55,789
Sit down, man.

1593
01:38:58,168 --> 01:38:59,128
(SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

1594
01:39:04,055 --> 01:39:05,892
So, you're here to kill me?

1595
01:39:05,934 --> 01:39:08,147
Nah, that's not really
what I do.

1596
01:39:08,189 --> 01:39:09,525
I mean, I might set you up
to get killed.

1597
01:39:09,566 --> 01:39:10,986
You know, facilitate it.

1598
01:39:11,028 --> 01:39:12,322
What are you looking for?

1599
01:39:14,743 --> 01:39:16,080
I don't know, my assassin?

1600
01:39:16,122 --> 01:39:18,877
Your assassin?
Yeah, and what do you think?

1601
01:39:18,919 --> 01:39:20,171
What does an assassin look like?

1602
01:39:20,213 --> 01:39:22,634
I mean,
it can kinda be anyone, huh?

1603
01:39:22,676 --> 01:39:24,680
I mean,
even a slight little nerdy fella

1604
01:39:24,722 --> 01:39:26,642
-likes to work on computers.
-Mm.

1605
01:39:26,684 --> 01:39:28,104
Only thing dangerous
about him is

1606
01:39:28,146 --> 01:39:30,901
he's got this dream
about rehabbing a Cessna,

1607
01:39:30,943 --> 01:39:34,074
just to fly it around to prove
to himself that he's not afraid.

1608
01:39:34,116 --> 01:39:38,041
(SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

1609
01:39:39,919 --> 01:39:41,088
These are killer, by the way.

1610
01:39:42,633 --> 01:39:44,303
Mm.
I'm gonna show you something.

1611
01:39:46,725 --> 01:39:48,562
Uh-oh.

1612
01:39:48,604 --> 01:39:50,566
(LAUGHS) I gotta hand it to you.
I almost didn't recognize you.

1613
01:39:51,150 --> 01:39:53,489
I said to the team, "Nah,
there's no way. That ain't him."

1614
01:39:53,530 --> 01:39:54,532
What do you want?

1615
01:39:54,574 --> 01:39:55,910
Honestly...

1616
01:39:57,120 --> 01:39:58,499
just here to save your life.

1617
01:39:58,540 --> 01:39:59,501
Oh.

1618
01:40:00,753 --> 01:40:02,298
How are you gonna do that?

1619
01:40:02,340 --> 01:40:03,801
Chuck, you killed three people.

1620
01:40:04,260 --> 01:40:06,807
Are you done?
Have you had enough?

1621
01:40:06,848 --> 01:40:08,477
No. I want the guy who pulled
the trigger. I want 'em all.

1622
01:40:08,519 --> 01:40:09,980
Damn, dude.

1623
01:40:10,022 --> 01:40:12,026
Well, that's
pretty cold-blooded.

1624
01:40:12,068 --> 01:40:14,572
You think they're gonna
let you leave Russia?

1625
01:40:14,614 --> 01:40:16,409
I mean, how does that even work?
How do you leave here?

1626
01:40:16,451 --> 01:40:17,955
The only way you leave here
is in a box.

1627
01:40:17,996 --> 01:40:20,251
But if you walk out of here
right now with me,

1628
01:40:20,292 --> 01:40:22,004
I can help you.

1629
01:40:22,046 --> 01:40:24,008
Nobody sent me.
I'm here on my own.

1630
01:40:25,094 --> 01:40:26,764
Shit, maybe you got a future
in this field.

1631
01:40:26,806 --> 01:40:28,517
Maybe we can figure
something out like that, huh?

1632
01:40:28,559 --> 01:40:29,687
-Just come home with me.
-(CHARLIE LAUGHS)

1633
01:40:29,728 --> 01:40:30,939
I have a future in the field?

1634
01:40:32,734 --> 01:40:35,447
Well, I could have sworn
you just said I have no future.

1635
01:40:36,408 --> 01:40:37,786
Look, I'm not gonna sit here
and pretend like

1636
01:40:37,828 --> 01:40:39,080
I understand
what's goin' on with you.

1637
01:40:39,122 --> 01:40:40,667
I don't, okay?
I've never felt that.

1638
01:40:40,709 --> 01:40:42,044
Your loss, I get it.

1639
01:40:43,172 --> 01:40:44,800
But you honored her.

1640
01:40:44,842 --> 01:40:46,052
What do you think she wants?

1641
01:40:46,094 --> 01:40:47,263
You think she wants you
to die here

1642
01:40:47,305 --> 01:40:48,850
in this country
with these people?

1643
01:40:49,894 --> 01:40:51,062
She would want you home, man.

1644
01:40:52,649 --> 01:40:53,568
No. I--

1645
01:40:54,361 --> 01:40:55,405
I can't go home.

1646
01:40:56,908 --> 01:40:57,826
Why?

1647
01:40:59,914 --> 01:41:01,626
She's not-- She's not there.

1648
01:41:09,016 --> 01:41:10,393
Okay.

1649
01:41:10,978 --> 01:41:12,899
You keep your head
on a swivel now, okay, Chuck?

1650
01:41:12,941 --> 01:41:13,816
Mm.

1651
01:41:18,076 --> 01:41:19,955
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1652
01:41:22,376 --> 01:41:25,215
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

1653
01:41:26,259 --> 01:41:27,010
(EXHALES)

1654
01:41:34,316 --> 01:41:37,949
(MEN SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

1655
01:42:21,370 --> 01:42:22,706
Sir, I'm sor-- sorry.

1656
01:42:22,748 --> 01:42:23,958
Do you speak English?

1657
01:42:24,627 --> 01:42:25,754
(SPEAKS RUSSIAN)

1658
01:42:25,796 --> 01:42:27,716
Sorry, sir. I'm sorry.

1659
01:42:27,758 --> 01:42:29,135
There were two men.

1660
01:42:30,179 --> 01:42:32,225
With you on a truck.

1661
01:42:33,102 --> 01:42:35,022
(SPEAKS RUSSIAN)

1662
01:42:42,538 --> 01:42:45,961
-(MACHINES WHIRRING)
-(JACKHAMMERS RATTLING)

1663
01:43:14,185 --> 01:43:16,940
(SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

1664
01:43:22,619 --> 01:43:24,497
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1665
01:43:27,085 --> 01:43:28,213
(GRUNTS)

1666
01:43:49,506 --> 01:43:50,591
(GRUNTS)

1667
01:44:01,780 --> 01:44:03,826
(GRUNTS)

1668
01:44:04,786 --> 01:44:05,831
(GROANING)

1669
01:44:38,062 --> 01:44:40,525
It's not very impressive, is it?

1670
01:44:40,567 --> 01:44:43,365
Placed near the cargo
you have below those hatches?

1671
01:44:44,074 --> 01:44:46,954
I think I might even feel
a little insulted.

1672
01:44:49,335 --> 01:44:51,214
-Who's coming after me?
-CHARLIE: Me.

1673
01:44:51,839 --> 01:44:54,303
-Me. I'm coming after you.
-Mm.

1674
01:44:54,887 --> 01:44:56,349
And who is running you?

1675
01:44:56,808 --> 01:44:58,645
What, are you afraid
Director Moore

1676
01:44:58,687 --> 01:45:00,774
has finally decided
to call it quits?

1677
01:45:00,816 --> 01:45:02,569
-Have you shut down?
-Mm.

1678
01:45:02,946 --> 01:45:04,782
Whatever you think you know...

1679
01:45:04,825 --> 01:45:07,371
I know Moore and Caleb
hire you and your outfit

1680
01:45:07,413 --> 01:45:08,833
to carry out black ops for them.

1681
01:45:08,874 --> 01:45:10,127
I have proof.

1682
01:45:10,585 --> 01:45:15,470
But, uh, that's not
what this is about, is it?

1683
01:45:16,932 --> 01:45:17,684
CHARLIE: No.

1684
01:45:21,149 --> 01:45:23,194
I came here
to face my wife's killer.

1685
01:45:25,575 --> 01:45:27,035
To look him in the eyes.

1686
01:45:28,329 --> 01:45:30,501
And tell him she mattered.

1687
01:45:32,797 --> 01:45:34,342
Sarah mattered.

1688
01:45:36,263 --> 01:45:38,976
So, it is just you. Hmm?

1689
01:45:40,980 --> 01:45:44,112
Gretchen, Blazhic, Ellish...

1690
01:45:44,154 --> 01:45:46,700
the men that, uh,
they sent after you.

1691
01:45:46,742 --> 01:45:49,956
This whole thing
is all your revenge?

1692
01:45:49,999 --> 01:45:51,752
Charlie's revenge?

1693
01:45:53,923 --> 01:45:55,009
(CHUCKLES)

1694
01:45:56,762 --> 01:45:57,764
Please.

1695
01:46:08,870 --> 01:46:11,375
I, uh-- I remember your wife.

1696
01:46:13,672 --> 01:46:15,717
She took the place
of someone else.

1697
01:46:15,968 --> 01:46:17,596
It's very, very brave.

1698
01:46:18,849 --> 01:46:21,395
I am sorry she died.

1699
01:46:21,646 --> 01:46:23,441
But it was...

1700
01:46:23,483 --> 01:46:24,610
necessary.

1701
01:46:25,069 --> 01:46:27,240
The police had blocked our exit.

1702
01:46:28,033 --> 01:46:31,541
I had to demonstrate
what would happen

1703
01:46:31,583 --> 01:46:33,879
if they did not allow us
to leave.

1704
01:46:34,338 --> 01:46:35,632
That-- That's it?

1705
01:46:38,597 --> 01:46:39,891
"Necessary"?

1706
01:46:40,601 --> 01:46:43,481
You are not
so different to me...

1707
01:46:43,523 --> 01:46:47,281
killing these people
to find your way here to me.

1708
01:46:48,700 --> 01:46:50,245
Has it made you feel better?

1709
01:46:51,789 --> 01:46:53,251
I won't know
till I've killed you.

1710
01:46:56,926 --> 01:46:58,428
It was...

1711
01:46:59,472 --> 01:47:01,894
-an instant. Your wife.
-No, it wasn't.

1712
01:47:01,936 --> 01:47:03,731
Yet you tortured
my colleagues...

1713
01:47:03,773 --> 01:47:06,319
dropped a man 16 stories...

1714
01:47:06,361 --> 01:47:09,868
suffocated a woman
in a-- a locked chamber.

1715
01:47:09,910 --> 01:47:12,456
You had them all unarmed,
defenseless.

1716
01:47:12,498 --> 01:47:16,799
Staged your elaborate murders
from a distance.

1717
01:47:16,840 --> 01:47:18,426
And you know why?

1718
01:47:21,391 --> 01:47:22,519
I do.

1719
01:47:24,105 --> 01:47:28,154
Because it's hard
to take a life up close.

1720
01:47:28,864 --> 01:47:33,332
You lose something each time.

1721
01:47:33,666 --> 01:47:36,588
A piece of yourself
you cannot get back ever.

1722
01:47:38,634 --> 01:47:42,100
And you've lost so much already.

1723
01:47:42,142 --> 01:47:44,521
So, you had to
give them a chance

1724
01:47:44,563 --> 01:47:45,857
to escape the mouse trap...

1725
01:47:45,898 --> 01:47:48,738
to run just fast enough.

1726
01:47:50,783 --> 01:47:52,787
Because then
you can tell yourself

1727
01:47:52,829 --> 01:47:55,209
there's no blood on your hands.

1728
01:47:55,251 --> 01:47:58,674
But doesn't mean you're weak.

1729
01:47:58,716 --> 01:48:02,640
Just means
you are not truly a killer.

1730
01:48:05,898 --> 01:48:07,192
Don't believe me?

1731
01:48:17,838 --> 01:48:19,091
(GUN CLICKS)

1732
01:48:21,513 --> 01:48:22,723
Go ahead.

1733
01:48:23,683 --> 01:48:26,272
You're here to kill me.
Take it. You'll see.

1734
01:48:28,276 --> 01:48:30,113
It's not a trick. Here.

1735
01:48:34,330 --> 01:48:36,251
All right, then. Huh?

1736
01:48:37,294 --> 01:48:39,048
End it face-to-face.

1737
01:48:43,140 --> 01:48:44,725
A friend of mine once told me

1738
01:48:44,767 --> 01:48:46,396
I'd never be able
to pull the trigger.

1739
01:48:48,733 --> 01:48:52,408
But he also said
I'd never be able to kill.

1740
01:49:33,282 --> 01:49:34,660
There it is.

1741
01:49:37,916 --> 01:49:39,503
That's what I came here for.

1742
01:49:41,340 --> 01:49:43,302
To balance the scales.

1743
01:49:46,725 --> 01:49:50,191
To make you feel what she felt
in that moment.

1744
01:49:51,694 --> 01:49:53,281
Before you killed her.

1745
01:50:07,935 --> 01:50:08,937
(EXHALES SLIGHTLY)

1746
01:50:16,076 --> 01:50:17,747
(BOAT GROANS)

1747
01:50:20,544 --> 01:50:21,379
(SPEAKING GERMAN) Was ist das?

1748
01:50:26,096 --> 01:50:28,185
(SHOUTING IN GERMAN)

1749
01:50:29,729 --> 01:50:30,981
Was ist das?

1750
01:50:32,068 --> 01:50:33,320
I've taken us on a detour.

1751
01:50:33,362 --> 01:50:35,115
Huh? Bullshit.

1752
01:50:35,157 --> 01:50:37,453
CHARLIE:
I've taken control of your boat.

1753
01:50:38,080 --> 01:50:39,624
We've just reached
Finnish waters.

1754
01:50:41,002 --> 01:50:42,004
(MAN SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

1755
01:50:42,046 --> 01:50:43,465
(COMPUTER BEEPING)

1756
01:50:43,507 --> 01:50:45,219
That is not possible.

1757
01:50:45,761 --> 01:50:47,974
This ship is a vault.

1758
01:50:48,016 --> 01:50:50,270
Your own CIA insisted upon it.

1759
01:50:50,312 --> 01:50:52,233
CHARLIE:
Using encryption I wrote.

1760
01:50:52,901 --> 01:50:54,822
Look, it's all running
from my hotel room.

1761
01:50:54,863 --> 01:50:56,951
These two may have
smashed my phone,

1762
01:50:56,992 --> 01:50:58,412
but they held on to theirs...

1763
01:50:58,746 --> 01:51:00,207
and my watch.

1764
01:51:00,249 --> 01:51:02,671
So, I'm the transmitter
and you...

1765
01:51:03,463 --> 01:51:05,134
you invited me in.

1766
01:51:05,844 --> 01:51:08,933
I just needed you to talk as
long as it took to get us here.

1767
01:51:09,685 --> 01:51:11,730
-(KLAXON BLARING)
-(SHIP HORN BLOWS)

1768
01:51:12,273 --> 01:51:15,572
That would be
the Finnish Navy and Interpol.

1769
01:51:15,822 --> 01:51:17,241
I gave them this location.

1770
01:51:18,327 --> 01:51:20,832
(SHIP HORN BLARING)

1771
01:51:20,874 --> 01:51:23,171
MAN: (OVER P.A.)
We are boarding your boat.

1772
01:51:23,212 --> 01:51:26,927
We are acting in accordance
with international law.

1773
01:51:27,596 --> 01:51:30,017
You are being placed
under arrest.

1774
01:51:32,314 --> 01:51:34,526
-(KLAXON BLARING)
-(REPEATING MESSAGE IN GERMAN)

1775
01:51:34,818 --> 01:51:36,489
Stand down, stand down!

1776
01:51:38,075 --> 01:51:39,286
Down.

1777
01:51:39,328 --> 01:51:41,540
(MEN SHOUTING IN RUSSIAN)

1778
01:51:41,582 --> 01:51:42,542
Heller.

1779
01:51:42,584 --> 01:51:43,837
Charlie Heller.

1780
01:51:43,879 --> 01:51:45,841
(SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)

1781
01:51:46,133 --> 01:51:48,304
All right.

1782
01:51:48,346 --> 01:51:50,058
(SPEAKS RUSSIAN)

1783
01:51:56,613 --> 01:51:59,326
-(HELICOPTER RATTLING)
-(MAN SHOUTS)

1784
01:52:01,205 --> 01:52:04,419
(MEN SHOUTING IN DISTANCE)

1785
01:52:09,806 --> 01:52:13,522
(HELICOPTER WHIRRING)

1786
01:52:25,379 --> 01:52:29,304
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

1787
01:52:49,887 --> 01:52:51,514
(EXHALES)

1788
01:52:54,312 --> 01:52:56,232
When I took up this role...

1789
01:52:57,068 --> 01:53:00,032
I made it clear to everyone
who works in this building,

1790
01:53:00,074 --> 01:53:02,078
that even though our work

1791
01:53:02,119 --> 01:53:04,958
sometimes goes on
in dark corners,

1792
01:53:05,000 --> 01:53:07,506
that is no excuse
to allow darkness

1793
01:53:07,547 --> 01:53:10,595
to obscure our objectives
or our methods.

1794
01:53:12,391 --> 01:53:14,603
So, I'm deeply saddened
to have to tell you

1795
01:53:14,645 --> 01:53:17,192
that information has surfaced

1796
01:53:17,234 --> 01:53:19,655
that implicates senior members
of this agency

1797
01:53:19,697 --> 01:53:22,077
in carrying out
rogue missions,

1798
01:53:22,411 --> 01:53:24,790
which put the safety
of our own operators

1799
01:53:24,832 --> 01:53:27,379
and agents we work with
at great risk.

1800
01:53:27,421 --> 01:53:28,798
Gentlemen.

1801
01:53:29,341 --> 01:53:32,180
O'BRIEN: The cost of winning
the war cannot be our honor.

1802
01:53:32,848 --> 01:53:34,727
Those operations
were not sanctioned.

1803
01:53:35,603 --> 01:53:37,691
They were illegal.

1804
01:53:37,984 --> 01:53:40,405
And those individuals will face
the full force of the law.

1805
01:53:41,783 --> 01:53:43,286
I will now take questions.

1806
01:53:43,661 --> 01:53:44,748
REPORTER: Washington Post.

1807
01:53:45,248 --> 01:53:46,793
I understand these arrests
are linked to...

1808
01:53:46,835 --> 01:53:49,716
a series of killings
in European cities last year.

1809
01:53:49,758 --> 01:53:52,304
Was the CIA involved
in those operations?

1810
01:53:52,345 --> 01:53:54,851
O'BRIEN: You would not
expect me to answer that.

1811
01:53:54,893 --> 01:53:56,646
REPORTER 2:
NBC. Is the whistleblower

1812
01:53:56,688 --> 01:53:58,609
still employed by the agency?

1813
01:53:58,650 --> 01:54:01,238
O'BRIEN: I can confirm
that the officer is safe.

1814
01:54:01,615 --> 01:54:03,702
And that they will continue
to serve with the agency.

1815
01:54:47,749 --> 01:54:49,210
Who's the Uber driver now?

1816
01:54:51,298 --> 01:54:52,676
You must be
running out of lives.

1817
01:54:52,718 --> 01:54:54,972
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

1818
01:54:55,014 --> 01:54:56,517
And you keep on
surprising me, Charlie.

1819
01:54:57,603 --> 01:54:59,022
Everything you taught me.

1820
01:54:59,063 --> 01:55:02,194
No, no. What you've done,
what you've become...

1821
01:55:02,236 --> 01:55:03,531
can't teach that.

1822
01:55:05,493 --> 01:55:07,789
I guess I just suddenly saw
what needed doing.

1823
01:55:07,831 --> 01:55:08,791
Yeah.

1824
01:55:09,668 --> 01:55:11,172
When no one else did.

1825
01:55:12,507 --> 01:55:13,426
Thank you.

1826
01:55:15,680 --> 01:55:16,933
(EXHALES)

1827
01:55:19,897 --> 01:55:21,484
See you around, Charlie.

1828
01:55:25,116 --> 01:55:25,910
(TAPS)

1829
01:55:34,218 --> 01:55:35,220
(ENGINE STARTS)

